text:
в наличии ♥️
кубик слон - это яркий развивающий тренажёр для вашего ребенка. 
яркая и веселая подвеска на коляску или кроватку.
красочное оформление, разнофактурность, колечко для подвешивания, забавный носик - всё это поможет сенсорному и эмоциональному развитию вашего малыша, подарит ему радость. звуковые элементы привлекают внимание, забавный образ слона и элементы игры обеспечивают эмоциональное развитие малыша.
у слона имеется:
- забавная мордочка с вышивкой и аппликацией
- звуковой элемент
- разнофактурные материалы /хлопок, трикотаж/
- колечки для подвешивания на коляску / кроватку

для развития:
- мелкой моторики
- слухового восприятия
- зрительного восприятия
- эмоционального восприятия - речевого развития

мякиши идеально подходят для самых маленьких, поскольку у них нет острых углов. удачно подобранный размер, цвет, звук, яркие и понятные рисунки развивают мышление, координацию движений и совершенствуют моторику нежных детских пальчиков.

text:
top 10 talks of ims 2018: sexual harassment in dj culture
.
for too long sexual misconduct has not only been rife but it’s even been glamourised in the music industry. today, the rise of collectives such as shesaidso, bolstered by widespread initiatives like #metoo, are helping to address the issue and change the conversation. in this discussion, we learn how sexual harassment and other misconduct is manifesting in dj culture and explore solutions that will not only minimise and put an end to these scenarios but also lead to fundamental changes in dance music as it relates to diversity and inclusion.

text:
в наличии
12+ мес.
в красочном мире пустышек physio каждый день новая улыбка!
удовлетворяет естественную потребность ребенка в сосании. 
научный комитет, включающий преподавателей университета ортодонтии, исследовал ортодонтическую соску chicco. 
рабочая группа проанализировала результаты научных исследований и выделила наиболее важные аспекты правильного применения сосок и характеристик, которыми они должны обладать. 
небольшие выступы на конце соски определяют положение кончика языка при движении вверх во время сосания и глотания. 
ультратонкий профиль узкой части соски позволяет малышу правильно закрывать рот.

text:
#tilmittforsvar 
i forsvaret e det _absolutt_ ikkje rom for seksuell trakassering.

sjefa, kollega, soldata: e du vitne til seksuelt nedlatanes kommentara eller oppførsel, ta ansvar, sei ifra og stå opp for de som rammes. som denna kampanjen vise, e det vanskelig å sei ifra sjøl.

hærens sjefssersjant skreiv følganes i sakens anledning: "(..)slik oppførsel er ikke forenelig med å være soldat og de fortjener ikke privilegiet å bære uniform. en norsk soldat verner om våre verdier. dette er å undergrave alt vi står for og alt vi er. vi tolererer det ikke! ferdig snakka." veldig tydelig. veldig bra! synes det e godt gjort av #forsvaretsforum å reagere på at #metoo -kampanjen glei forbi forsvaret, som om problemet ikke finnes der.

respekt til de som har stått fram. det kreve mot:

text:
¿recién ahora hablás?
.
. **** .
.
"me parece desubicado que vengas con esta cuestión ahora; si no hablaste en su momento, lo lamento, ya es tarde". a lo largo de mi vida escuché este tipo de sentencias en varias oportunidades y al escucharlas algo en mí flaqueaba y yo proseguía como si lo afirmado fuera verdad: no, no tengo derecho a reflotar temas ásperos del pasado; debería haber hablado antes.

pero la experiencia, sanar mi alma, escucharme y aprender a escuchar, me demostraron lo contrario: nunca es tarde para hablar.

entonces, ante la pregunta de por qué no lo hablé en el momento, hoy ya no me paralizo ni quedo desdibujada:

a veces no hablamos porque nuestras emociones, nuestro ser y todo lo que nos compone, no siempre son capaces de asimilar ni analizar las situaciones en ese presente, hasta que un día nos despertamos y la realidad se revela, logramos identificarla y, entonces, comprendemos.

y, a veces, es por miedo; otras, porque sentimos vergüenza. "¿cómo no te diste la media vuelta en el momento? yo no lo hubiera tolerado un segundo", me dijeron cuando revelé una situación vivida en mi pasado. y, claro, tal vez por eso no hablamos, pareciera que el mundo está plagado de personas con la autoestima siempre alta, siempre instantáneas y llenas de orgullo. quizás por eso tampoco nos atrevemos, porque el mundo juzga, nos deja culpables y avergonzados por nuestra supuesta imperfección en una sociedad perfecta. 
pero entendí que los seres humanos tenemos esa mala tendencia a afirmar que reaccionaríamos de tal o cual forma, cuando no nos toca experimentar algo similar en primera persona. comprendí que no debe haber ni un alma en esta tierra que no haya atravesado por alguna situación sin saber cómo encararla en el momento, que tuvo que procesarla y sólo pudo volverla voz y acción mucho tiempo después. text:
i have been reluctant to post about this because i still have a lot of victim guilt of “how could i let this happen to me.” but my former creative director constantly favored the boys, counted me out and stuck me on chick teams, and was grossly inappropriate in so, so many ways (how many employees have had to watch their boss get a lap dance?) his behavior inspired the bad boy boss in my novel copygirl. 
i worked under him for years. without saying a peep and just watched his star rise, unfettered. glad some young, brave souls at his recent post spoke up and did what i couldn’t. i thought he was untouchable. too powerful. but we all have power in us we don’t even know.  you can read about his fall here: ‪ ‪http://bit.ly/2dsvmlo ‬

mira como nos ponemos con tu complicidad. 
mira como nos ponemos con tu violencia. 
mira como nos ponemos con tus injusticias. 
mira como nos ponemos con tu silencio. 
mira como nos ponemos con tus amenazas 
mira como nos ponemos con tu prepotencia.

mira como nos ponemos ahora que estamos juntas. 
mira como nos ponemos ahora que si nos ven. 
mira como nos ponemos ahora que si nos creen.
se va a caer porque lo vamos a tirar.

text:
#starstoday 
cuando uno observa eventos colectivos y mira el cielo, no hay error. a veces es tan exacto que parece que lo mandaron a hacer. 
hoy #mercurio entra en sagitario por segunda vez este año. mercurio es entendimiento y comunicación. mercurio en sagitario es “cuenta tu historia y hazlo en grande, cuenta tu experiencia”. -la historia -

mercurio llegó a sagitario -donde tiene un megáfono- el 31 de octubre, pero se devolvió a escorpio donde se tratan temas oscuros, temas que usualmente se quedan debajo del tapete. 
para ese momento venus (energía femenina) también estaba moviéndose retrógrada entre escorpio (esa misma energía oculta) y libra (los lineamientos para quedar bien). desde ese momento hasta acá han pasado muchas cosas: tuvimos el venus star point que habla de un ciclo de ocho años que llega a su final. en un punto se vieron mercurio y venus de vuelta a escorpio, porque un asunto oculto debía verse de frente. los nodos entraron en cáncer y capricornio: con los próximos eclipses volveremos a casa, pero solo después de dar un hit al sistema que nos ha regido siempre porque no da más. 
y aquí estamos... tal como dije al inicio, hoy mercurio entra en sagitario. no importa del país que seas o si no entiendes por qué estoy contando esto así. es responsabilidad de todos hacer espacio para expresar verdades que pueden cambiar el sistema que no funciona. desde que júpiter entró en escorpio (de octubre 2017- noviembre 2018), historias ocultas de abuso de poder han estado saliendo a la luz aunque ha sucedido toda la vida. todos alguna vez hemos sido tratados de manera no adecuada porque supuestamente no somos adecuados. miren más allá de los abusos sexuales, de poder, los hay de todo tipo amparados por religión, cultura, por nacionalidad. reglas hechas por el hombre. tenemos que salir del piloto automático y despertar para iniciar el cambio que todos necesitamos. 
para finalizar, tienen que saber que si no cuentan su historia nadie la va a contar desde la verdad. que si no usan su poder personal, alguien más lo usará sobre uds. que al buscar cómo expresar tu historia es que terminas de contarla... #astrology #astrología #astrokabbalah #metoo

para finalizar, tienen que saber que si no cuentan su historia nadie la va a contar desde la verdad. que si no usan su poder personal, alguien más lo usará sobre uds. que al buscar cómo expresar tu historia es que terminas de contarla...

text:
no llama la atención que de acá a la china sea el mismo problema siempre. resulta que aunque haya varias denuncias, si no hay prueba de que eso pasó, es inocente. ¿pero cómo prueban ellos que no pasó? tampoco, pero la fácil es no creernos.
igual que acá... donde por ejemplo a un internista bastante conocido de una prepaga llamada colsánitas y que atiende por la 127 es declarado inocente por el tribunal de ética médica por "falta de pruebas" tras manosearnos a varias en consulta. [y gracias al tribunal de ética médica puede seguir manoseando porque de los manoseos no quedan pruebas].
5 denuncias no son suficiente para un tribunal de ética médica tan o más viciado por el colegaje que otras mafias, pero igual de oscuro. donde en mi caso personal hasta uno de los argumentos para dudar de mi y no de él fue que mi ex marido volvió a consulta donde ese médico luego del acoso. no podían tener en cuenta que tenía toda la historia clínica de toda su vida allá y debía ir, no, era más fácil hacer la fácil: pensar que las mujeres que denunciamos somos locas, inventamos, porque siempre dudan de nosotras primero, ¿o no?
el argumento de él ... que complotamos para denunciarlo.. bla bla bla. ¿por qué uno va a tener ganas de perder tiempo o inventar cosas con la humillación que implica ir a denunciar algo que pasó? ¿es en serio? si, es en serio.
otras tantas que no se animaron, 3 de ellas prescribieron (+ de 5 años). y así.. por allá sigue el hombre, en consulta. ¿y cuántos así no? por todos lados, siguen con impunidad porque total no nos creen. por eso siguen, hasta que seamos más fuertes que el miedo.
denunciar, sin miedo porque para eso estamos todas: para no darnos la espalda cuando otros la dan. porque hablar no se hace por una misma, se hace por todas!
así que, obvio me sumo... y acá cuántas deberíamos ponernos... mirá como nos ponemos!!
#yonotengomiedo
#yositecreo
#metoo
#yotambien
#mirácomonosponemos
pd: si al leer lo del médico y sospechas quien puede ser porque te pasó, escribime que te doy la dirección del tribunal. mandar la carta es fácil, y no es por vos, es por las que vienen después. 
sea cual sea el caso, hablá que te apoyamos, una somos todas.

text:
does christmas bring you 'joy or pain'?
we are inbuilt to think christmas is a happy time, a time to share, a time to give, a time to be with loved ones, to remember loved ones, to eat more, drink more, have more....but what about those around you who don't enjoy this season. 
are you aware of that person at work who is not looking forward to christmas, or the friend who has no-one but is happy to be on their own this christmas, or the family around the corner who have nothing. maybe they could benefit from you, maybe they could enjoy a bit of company, maybe they could receive a nice donation of food.

maybe you are suffering at this time of year and don't know where to turn and are scared to reach out. don't be. there is support everywhere at this time of year, for us all. there is someone somewhere willing to support you, and if you are in doubt, how about calling the samaritans 116 123. 
today i am went to piaroos wish, helping the homeless in reading to support those in need at this time of year. it is colder, darker and harder. can you imagine if you had nothing?

when was the last time you stopped and spoke to someone on the streets or someone vulnerable around you? take a minute if you can and try it. you will be amazed at how important those few minutes could be to someone else. i love giving my time to others, and i thank those who have given their time to me. 
as i head into my festive season with my loved ones, i thank you all for supporting me this year in all of my activities. it has been an amazing year in so many ways, and i have learnt so much. but most of all i have learnt the value of giving back, in a much stronger way then i have ever done before. i have learnt the importance of my community and the strength everyone brings to my life, www.emmajanetaylor.life

when was the last time you stopped and spoke to someone on the streets or someone vulnerable around you? take a minute if you can and try it. you will be amazed at how important those few minutes could be to someone else. i love giving my time to others, and i thank those who have given their time to me. 
as i head into my festive season with my loved ones, i thank you all for supporting me this year in all of my activities. it has been an amazing year in so many ways, and i have learnt so much. but most of all i have learnt the value of giving back, in a much stronger way then i have ever done before. i have learnt the importance of my community and the strength everyone brings to my life, www.emmajanetaylor.life

text:
jamal khashoggi fue nombrado "persona del año 2018" por la revista time

el periodista saudí asesinado jamal khashoggi, junto con otros tres reporteros y un medio de comunicación, fueron designados hoy como persona del año 2018 por la revista time. "este año estamos reconociendo cuatro periodistas y un medio de comunicación que han pagado un terrible precio por encarar los desafíos de este momento", indicó edward felsenthal, director de la publicación neoyorquina, en un comunicado.

junto khashoggi, también fueron destacados la periodista filipina maria ressa, editora del portal de noticias rappler, muy crítico con el presidente filipino, rodrigo duterte; y los reporteros de la agencia reuters wa lone y kyaw soe oo, detenidos por las autoridades de birmania mientras investigaban las atrocidades cometidas contra la minoría rohingya.

asimismo, el periódico local capital gazette, de annapolis (maryland), donde cinco reporteros resultaron muertos en un tiroteo este año.

los integrantes del movimiento #metoo, en su mayoría mujeres, fueron elegidos como persona del año en la última edición, en 2017.
.
.
.
.
#noticias #news #12dic #londrestv

text:
#barbietoo  before i left the house i made sure to dress in something loose that would not be too distracting. as i walk the streets of new york at night,one hand holds my groceries tightly, the other holds my pocket knife. i walk with urgency, my hoodie is up and my headphones in and,which are not playing music, act like a barrier between the men who catcalls and whistles at me. i see a masculine shadow at the end of the street, but i cannot see its owner. i fear it’s a man awaiting my passing. i make a detour and walk across the street. 
as i usually do on a weekend night, i was clubbing and hanging out with my girls. i normally go to gay clubs, but this weekend i went to a straight club.  once i felt a strong grip on my ass, i turned around to say what the hell, but this 6 foot tall frat guy in a polo would not look at me. this is the first time i  had my ass grabbed unsolicitedly. they have the balls to grab me, but they don’t own up to their actions. every 5 minutes i would take a headcount of my girls because the cocky boys would not listen to us when we said we did not want to grind with them. this was the first night where i saw that the boys were not listening to no. it made me wonder why they felt because it was dark and the music was loud that they could do what they want. i was not being listened to. “there is no greater threat to women than men? we’re the number one threat!” said louis c.k. in his hbo special. when are men taught to acknowledge boundaries? i should be able to leave and feel safe wherever i go without having to worry. i am tired with the way that men are treating me and other women. every women has there own story with harassment, but to tell mine i am using barbie as my proxy. when i was younger i looked up to her and she was a beacon of indepence and i vividly remember watching rapunzel barbie in my bubblegum pink room thinking “look at all that she can do for herself”. #photo #photography #art #camera #canon #fujifilm #fujitx1 #digital #digitalphoto #digitalphotography #digitalphotos #mirrorless #metoo #barbie #pink #hair #violent #ken #sexualassult

text:
when you understand this you will not be deceived again. the bible doesn't require women to love their husband but to honor their husband. women are incapable of loving a man the way a man loves a woman. they will say they can, but they only perceive through a woman's mind. they are conditional creatures and their love is based on feelings. that is the equivalent of being a person that only works in certain temperatures. if a fire fighter says he will only leave the station in weather that is sunny, how effective would he be. if an airline company only flies during sunny weather between 80-90°, how long would they last. the male is a fire fighter that puts his life on the line 24hours no matter the threat to life and no matter the conditions. the woman doesn't submit or love 24 hours no matter the threat to her security no matter the conditions. they aren't malicious they are just not designed for it.

months ago i made a post that asked, who is the greatest predator of humans the lion or the shark. i used this question to describe how men and women think. a woman can say women can love, but she is viewing it based on her mindset and perception, which is rooted in emotions.

the shark is the greatest predator to humans because if you come across the shark you are in its environment. a man's mind is the human on land, the womans mind when compared to the man's is the human in the shark infested water. 
they are simply in the wrong territory when trying to debate with logic. the same can be said about men trying to understand a womans emotions and feelings, we can other naturally feel the way they do.

i said naturally because a man can artificially feel emotions and feelings the way a woman does through the use of drugs. there is no drug a woman can take that can make her think logically like a man. if a man wanted to feel what it is like to be in tuned so deeply with feelings there are plants in the amazon he can take, and he can even take pure molly. molly will have you feeling your emotions and feelings on a much deeper level than normally possible. we are two different creatures, so love rooted in emotions cannot be love, because true love is unconditional.

text:
todos deberiamos ser feministas. 
porque feminismo no significa poder de la mujer sobre el hombre, porque la búsqueda de la igualdad empieza por romper estructuras para el bien de todos. porque nadie merece menos que el otro, nadie es superior ni inferior.. porque es momento de escuchar y dejar de hablar sin saber. 
porque es momento de respetar, de aprender, todos debemos aprender, todos debemos nutrirnos de nuevas ideas, y enseñar a aquellos que están equivocados ... ayer en nuestro pais, #thelmafardin (actriz) denuncio legalmente a un actor que la violo cuando tenía 16 años.. me destroza ver que la gente aún está intentando defender cosas y acciones tan horripilantes como estas porque están en contra de un movimiento como el feminismo... cuando esto se trata de un crimen, de un acoso sexual, de una violación de uno de los derechos mas básicos de una persona. porfavor, es tiempo de dejar de creer en lo establecido, romper esas ideas que hemos naturalizado por años como creer que un hombre puede meter la mano donde no debe por el hecho de tener un "poder" que no le corresponde. es tiempo de apoyar a las víctimas y no levantarles un mural en frente. 
se que es dificil romper con la cultura que nos han inculcado... pero un crimen es un crimen, una violación es una violación, y las mujeres estamos cansadas de ser tomadas como objetos. 
nos cansamos.... #miracomonosponemos 
#jenniferlawrence #jlaw 
#argentina #metoo #igualdad #yotecreo

text:
#mirácómonosponemos

es el mensaje de miles de mujeres en las redes sociales que se unieron para apoyar la causa de la actriz @soythelmafardin, quien denunció por violación a juan darthés durante una gira que compartieron por la tira “patito feo”.
en una conferencia de prensa realizada junto al colectivo @actrices.argentinas, la joven contó en detalle cómo y cuándo ocurrieron los hechos: "me dijo que si yo accedía, me iba a garantizar trabajo. le dije que no y él siguió", fueron algunas de sus palabras que se escucharon con potencia.
pese al dolor, las muestras de apoyo fueron inmediatas. no solo de las colegas que le sostuvieron la mano en el escenario, como @griseldasiciliani, @lolafonca, @soyjazminstuart, @laliespositoo, @lauraazcurra y @lacalurivero, otra denunciante de darthés. también, lo hicieron a la distancia excompañeras de la novela juvenil como @basnicar y, además, @sangrejaponesa que pidió perdón públicamente por dichos del pasado. en cuanto a @ana.rosenfeld la abogada finalmente expuso porqué dejó la defensa del actor #metoo #metooargentina #niunamenos #pañueloverde

text:
a veces callarse es ser cómplice. y yo menos que nadie sería cómplice de una violación. 
no me copa hablar del tema darthes porque, aunque en este caso las probabilidades de que sea culpable son gigantes, hay una familia también detrás de él que con la sola sospecha ya se viene abajo.
para mí el #miracomonosponemos es para todos los abusadores. los que abusan física, verbal y psicológicamente de nosotras "porque pueden". sé bien que una mujer puede callarse por miedo, por no querer lastimar a su propia familia e, incluso pasados varios años, puede no querer confundir justicia con venganza. las razones por las cuales no hablamos pueden variar. pero lo que hoy quiero rescatar es que la violencia machista se tiene que terminar. ni una sóla mujer tiene que soportar maltratos, y no sólo el físico:
⚠ si te cela por todo, es maltrato.
⚠ si te hackea tus contraseñas, es maltrato.
⚠ si te habla mal de todo tu entorno para tenerte sólo para él, es maltrato.
⚠ si te revisa las llamadas, es maltrato.
⚠ si te dice con quien podes y con quien no podes seguir en contacto, es maltrato.
⚠ si por sus celos te dice puta, es maltrato.
⚠ si se para atrás tuyo para ver con quién chateas, es maltrato.
⚠ si te acusa de cosas que no hiciste, es maltrato.
⚠ si te psicopatea, es maltrato.
.
si tenes una amiga, familiar o conocida que pase por algo de esto, no te alejes porque se aleja, porque cuando ella se cierra es cuando más te necesita.
.
y a vos, si la piba esta llorando, no te besa y te da la espalda es porque no quiere, no seas violín 👊👊👊👊👊👊👊👊👊👊
.
.
#noesno #niunamenos #metoo

text:
🔺 ayer por la noche, los medios de comunicación argentinos informaron sobre la denuncia penal que interpuso la actriz thelma fardín, quien con 16 años fue violada por el actor juan darthés (45), cuando ambos trabajan en la serie infantil ‘patito feo’, transmitida por disney channel.
.
🔺 no es la primera vez que darthés es acusado de agresión o acoso sexual, las actrices calu rivero, anitta coacci y natalia juncos ya lo habían denunciado desde el año 1999, de hecho, la frase “mirá cómo me pones” ha sido una constante en las declaraciones de todas las víctimas, cuando contaban lo que el actor les decía al momento de acosarlas.
.
🔺 “mirá cómo nos ponemos: unidas, fuertes, frente a tu violencia y tu impunidad, nosotras estamos juntas. justicia para nuestra compañera, justicia para todas. esto recién empieza”, fue el mensaje con el que un colectivo de mujeres y actrices argentina dio, durante una conferencia realizada en apoyo a thelma, y que ha tenido una gran repercusión en todos los sectores de la sociedad argentina.
.
🔺nosotras hoy también alzamos nuestra voz ante la violencia y la impunidad. nos unimos a la lucha de thelma, de calu, de anitta y natalia, pero también a la de todas las mujeres que a diario tienen que lidiar con abuso y acoso sexual en sus trabajos, en la calle y en su casa.
.
🔸hermanas, nosotras sí les creemos🔸.
.
.
.
.

tweet_full:
🔺 ayer por la noche, los medios de comunicación argentinos informaron sobre la denuncia penal que interpuso la actriz thelma fardín, quien con 16 años fue violada por el actor juan darthés (45), cuando ambos trabajan en la serie infantil ‘patito feo’, transmitida por disney channel.
.
🔺 no es la primera vez que darthés es acusado de agresión o acoso sexual, las actrices calu rivero, anitta coacci y natalia juncos ya lo habían denunciado desde el año 1999, de hecho, la frase “mirá cómo me pones” ha sido una constante en las declaraciones de todas las víctimas, cuando contaban lo que el actor les decía al momento de acosarlas.
.
🔺 “mirá cómo nos ponemos: unidas, fuertes, frente a tu violencia y tu impunidad, nosotras estamos juntas. justicia para nuestra compañera, justicia para todas. esto recién empieza”, fue el mensaje con el que un colectivo de mujeres y actrices argentina dio, durante una conferencia realizada en apoyo a thelma, y que ha tenido una gran repercusión en todos los sectores de la sociedad argentina.
.
🔺nosotras hoy también alzamos nuestra voz ante la violencia y la impunidad. nos unimos a la lucha de thelma, de calu, de anitta y natalia, pero también a la de todas las mujeres que a diario tienen que lidiar con abuso y acoso sexual en sus trabajos, en la calle y en su casa.
.
🔸hermanas, nosotras sí les creemos🔸.
.
.
.
.

text:
🌸 so here i am gonna address the most prevalent problem in pakistan - child abuse. child abuse is a very sensitive issue that needs to be discussed so that people are aware about it. 
when we hear the term “child abuse" the only thing that comes to our mind is sexual harassment. but the most engrossing fact is that its not just sexual harassment.

child abuse can take any form : 
1) physical abuse (physical abuse is any forceful activity that can harm a child physically .its  when somebody purposely hurts a child like; beating, strangling) 
2) sexual abuse (sexual abuse is when an adult makes sexual contact with a child)
3) emotional abuse (when a child does not get the love and affection they deserve from  their parents/friends/classmates etc.)
4) neglect (when a child lacks things they need in order to grow like: shelter, education ,safety, etc.) following are the things we should consider doing:
1) it doesn't matter when child abuse has occured. your child needs counselling and care after such an incident.
2) make them emotionally strong.
3) you should be supportive and open to your child so they can share anything with you.
4) build a friendly relationship with them so they don't hesitate or feel ashamed sharing awkward situations they face. 
5) educate them on sexual harrasment. and teach them how to recognize the early signs and wrong touches.
6) keep a check on your child's activites.
7) don't trust any stranger with your child.
8) make them understand that its not their fault so that they never feel guilty about it.
9) dont let them feel lonely and listen to them carefully.
10) be a positive role model for your child. 
i hope you guys benefit from this message. share it with others aswell to spread awareness ❤ . . . . . . .

#childabuse.  #abuse.  #pstd.  #mentalhealth. #children.  #sexualabuse.  #abusesurvivor  #recovery. #metoo #trauma.  #blogger.  #peace.  #lifestyleblogger  #fashionblogger

text:
christopher wylie, the whistleblower who exposed the widespread misuse of data by his former employer, cambridge analytica, has revealed how the company “weaponised” the fashion industry in the run up to the 2016 us election, which he claims helped donald trump get elected.

speaking at the annual bof voices festival in oxfordshire, wylie revealed for the first time a matrix based on data collected by the firm which he claims can show how users’ preferences for particular brands on social media platforms – facebook, in particular – were then used to help target these same users with pro-trump messaging. he compared the misuse of fashion-based data as one of the campaign’s lesser reported “weapons of mass destruction”. - they [cambridge analytica] looked at actual people. how they engaged with certain brands was put into a funnel and helped build the algorithms, wylie explained. - when you look at personality traits, music and fashion are the most informative [tools] for predicting someone’s personality. a user’s predilection for a particular label gives, he said, a very clear indication of what reports often call “populist political signalling”. cambridge analytica, which was shut down earlier this year following an investigation by the observer, was the political marketing firm headed by trump’s former key adviser, steve bannon, and owned by hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. it also used user information obtained without authorisation in early 2014 – including cultural preferences such as fashion and music – to create a system that could single out voters in order to expose them to specific political advertising.

morwenna ferrier
the guardian

speaking at the annual bof voices festival in oxfordshire, wylie revealed for the first time a matrix based on data collected by the firm which he claims can show how users’ preferences for particular brands on social media platforms – facebook, in particular – were then used to help target these same users with pro-trump messaging. he compared the misuse of fashion-based data as one of the campaign’s lesser reported “weapons of mass destruction”. - they [cambridge analytica] looked at actual people. how they engaged with certain brands was put into a funnel and helped build the algorithms, wylie explained. - when you look at personality traits, music and fashion are the most informative [tools] for predicting someone’s personality. a user’s predilection for a particular label gives, he said, a very clear indication of what reports often call “populist political signalling”. cambridge analytica, which was shut down earlier this year following an investigation by the observer, was the political marketing firm headed by trump’s former key adviser, steve bannon, and owned by hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. it also used user information obtained without authorisation in early 2014 – including cultural preferences such as fashion and music – to create a system that could single out voters in order to expose them to specific political advertising.

morwenna ferrier
the guardian

text_retweet:
#repost @geripomato (@get_repost)
・・・
no llama la atención que de acá a la china sea el mismo problema siempre. resulta que aunque haya varias denuncias, si no hay prueba de que eso pasó, es inocente. ¿pero cómo prueban ellos que no pasó? tampoco, pero la fácil es no creernos.
igual que acá... donde por ejemplo a un internista bastante conocido de una prepaga llamada colsánitas y que atiende por la 127 es declarado inocente por el tribunal de ética médica por "falta de pruebas" tras manosearnos a varias en consulta. [y gracias al tribunal de ética médica puede seguir manoseando porque de los manoseos no quedan pruebas].
5 denuncias no son suficiente para un tribunal de ética médica tan o más viciado por el colegaje que otras mafias, pero igual de oscuro. donde en mi caso personal hasta uno de los argumentos para dudar de mi y no de él fue que mi ex marido volvió a consulta donde ese médico luego del acoso. no podían tener en cuenta que tenía toda la historia clínica de toda su vida allá y debía ir, no, era más fácil hacer la fácil: pensar que las mujeres que denunciamos somos locas, inventamos, porque siempre dudan de nosotras primero, ¿o no?
el argumento de él ... que complotamos para denunciarlo.. bla bla bla. ¿por qué uno va a tener ganas de perder tiempo o inventar cosas con la humillación que implica ir a denunciar algo que pasó? ¿es en serio? si, es en serio.
otras tantas que no se animaron, 3 de ellas prescribieron (+ de 5 años). y así.. por allá sigue el hombre, en consulta. ¿y cuántos así no? por todos lados, siguen con impunidad porque total no nos creen. por eso siguen, hasta que seamos más fuertes que el miedo.
denunciar, sin miedo porque para eso estamos todas: para no darnos la espalda cuando otros la dan. porque hablar no se hace por una misma, se hace por todas!
así que, obvio me sumo... y acá cuántas deberíamos ponernos... mirá como nos ponemos!!
#yonotengomiedo
#yositecreo
#metoo
#yotambien
#mirácomonosponemos
pd: si al leer lo del médico y sospechas quien puede ser porque te pasó, escribime que te doy la dirección del tribunal. mandar la carta es fácil, y no es por vos, es por las que vienen después.
sea cual sea el caso, hablá que te apoyamos

text:
(pude poner una foto de hombre como la de una mujer) 
en casa siempre se contaban historias y yo también las cuento ahora. ellas no enseñan a relacionarnos, a abrir los ojos, nos iluminan como un faro de auto en una ruta desierta; nos brinda la posibilidad de informarnos y nos da empatía hacia el otro. esta historia es la del: ¡no es no! para todos: para vos y para mi. lleve traje o vestido, tenga una linda sonrisa o vista bonito. ¡no es no! para vos o para mi. no importa el lugar que ocupe el veredicto de los demás: ¡no es no! -¿soy lo bastante buena para darme cuenta?
-sí - ¿puedo decir que no? - ¡por supuesto!
despojemos las pompas y el boato, tu vida puede cambiar para siempre. vamos juntas de la mano y trabajemos para que sea cómo debe ser. depende de todas nosotras. ¡tenés voz! ¡tenés el no! 
#mamafiaca #tenesvoz #teneselno #niunamenos #noesno #mujeres #madres #hijas #mama #niñas #metoo

text:
@lindsayjdraper don’t you wanna meet me at the gym?
.
by yourself or with a buddy, this one is a great workout! if your gym doesn’t have some of these things look around and see what they do have. you can always swap out exercises. 😉 we do the push ups and pull ups every week so we can master them and then switch out our circuits.
.
60 minutes-ish total body burner!
.
warm up: 10-15 minutes on a treadmill or stair master. get that ♥️ rate going so you’re ready to work!
.
1️⃣: 3 sets of push ups alternated with 3 sets of assisted pull-ups. set weight appropriately. *
.
2️⃣: 3 sets of push ups (yes, more push-ups) alternated with 3 sets of lat pull down.
.
3️⃣: circuit training!! i love this part of the workout. we each pick three exercise that sound fun to us that day and set our timer for 1:00 minute of work and 15 second of rest to rotate to the next exercise. repeat 2x through. todays circuit:
.
- battle ropes
- weighted squats with a ball (ouch, quads!)
- weighted bulgarian split lunge, one keg the first time through and then swap the second time through - tricep extensions with the cable
- tire flip
- burpees with a bicep curl and shoulder press
.
get out there and give this one a try! then post it in your stories and tag me in it.
.
*if you’ve never used this machine before it works differently than most machines. the goal here is to use less and less weight each time instead of more and more. if you chose 80lbs as your weight that means the machine is taking 80lbs off of your body weight. so 80 lbs less you’re pulling up. each time you head to the gym see if you can lower the number by just a few until you’re pulling up all your body weight!

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
trigger warning: mention of rape ⚠️ what was their fault? several people have been a victim of rape in this country, so many flowers were plucked before they could bloom, pure and innocent souls scarred for ever, their dreams and livelihood stolen from them, and pain and suffering is what was left.

rape does not just harm one physically but it is a mental trauma for the entire life. the survivors are scarred forever and get major mental health issues, like depression, insomnia, self neglecting, and so many more. it could also make one person suicidal and they could attempt to harm themselves.

what further deteriorates the situation is the lack of acceptance by the society for the victim. the survivor is blamed for the rape rather than the rapist, the clothes being too revealing is made a reason for blaming the victim. they are not accepted in this society and being a target of someone else's inhumanity results in their lives being destroyed whereas the rapist lives freely.

it's time for us to change. it's time for us to speak. it's time for us to fight for our rights. you are not responsible for it, someone else is, and they will bear the circumstances for doing such a thing, not you, because rape is wrong and its time to speak to stop the wrong. we can't let inhumane people ruin our lives, we can't let society blame the victim for being raped, and we will stand against the rape culture that exists in our society. it is time and you know it. -by sfm

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

🔺 ayer por la noche, los medios de comunicación argentinos informaron sobre la denuncia penal que interpuso la actriz thelma fardín, quien con 16 años fue violada por el actor juan darthés (45), cuando ambos trabajan en la serie infantil ‘patito feo’, transmitida por disney channel.
.
🔺 no es la primera vez que darthés es acusado de agresión o acoso sexual, las actrices calu rivero, anitta coacci y natalia juncos ya lo habían denunciado desde el año 1999, de hecho, la frase “mirá cómo me pones” ha sido una constante en las declaraciones de todas las víctimas, cuando contaban lo que el actor les decía al momento de acosarlas.
.
🔺 “mirá cómo nos ponemos: unidas, fuertes, frente a tu violencia y tu impunidad, nosotras estamos juntas. justicia para nuestra compañera, justicia para todas. esto recién empieza”, fue el mensaje con el que un colectivo de mujeres y actrices argentina dio, durante una conferencia realizada en apoyo a thelma, y que ha tenido una gran repercusión en todos los sectores de la sociedad argentina.
.
🔺nosotras hoy también alzamos nuestra voz ante la violencia y la impunidad. nos unimos a la lucha de thelma, de calu, de anitta y natalia, pero también a la de todas las mujeres que a diario tienen que lidiar con abuso y acoso sexual en sus trabajos, en la calle y en su casa.
.
🔸hermanas, nosotras sí les creemos🔸.
.
.
.
.

⠀
сегодня, когда я возвращалась из поликлиники, за мной следом шёл подвыпивший тип, внешне - браток из 90х. 
он вёл с кем-то оживленную беседу на слегка повышенных тонах. и тут я услышала: «передо мной тут девчонка такая красивая идёт!», обсудил с другом в подробностях все части моего тела, что ниже спины, и как бы он меня...
⠀
мне хотелось расплакаться от бессилия и того, насколько мне противно. ведь я - это не жопа. причём, одета я была более чем просто скромно: джинсы, кроссовки и дутый пуховик.
⠀
вот в америке и других развитых странах я могла бы его засудить. там у них вайнштейны и флешмобы #metoo . а у нас? пьяный вася громко на всю улицу тебя имеет. хоть и на словах. ⠀ ⠀
вот зачем нам нужен здравый феминизм, а не это вот все: «мужики х*емрази, а ты рабыня патриархата». мужчины! будьте мужчинами. пожалуйста!
обняла.

text:
.- un grupo numeroso de actrices argentinas denunció el martes públicamente la violación que sufrió la actriz thelma fardin cuando tenía 16 años por parte del actor juan darthés, pseudónimo de juan rafael pacífico dabul.
“acompañamos la denuncia penal de thelma fardin contra juan darthés”, señaló el colectivo actrices argentinas en un comunicado que leyeron de manera conjunta.
las artistas mostraron un vídeo en el que fardin relató los abusos a los que se vio sometida en 2009 en nicaragua, cuando era menor de edad y estaba de gira con un programa infantil.
“el único actor adulto que viajaba con nosotras tenía 45 años”, advirtió en esa grabación.
una noche “comenzó a besarme el cuello y le dije que no; me agarró la mano, me hizo que le tocara y me dijo ‘mira cómo me ponés’, haciéndome sentir su erección”, continuó fardin.
la actriz relató de manera pormenorizada los abusos que sufrió.
explicó que fue sometida a sexo oral y que luego fue penetrada, aunque ella seguía “diciendo que no”.
de nada sirvió que fardin le recordara a darthés que tenía la edad de sus hijos.
el abuso continuó hasta que “alguien tocó la puerta y yo pude salir de esa habitación”.
“gracias a que alguien habló, hoy puedo hablar”, dijo en alusión a una denuncia que realizó hace varios meses otra chica contra darthés, la cual no tuvo repercusión.
➡️www.eje21.com.co

text:
eva de dominici, quien en su momento había salido a defender a juan darthés tras las acusaciones de calu rivero, se mostró arrepentida y pidió disculpas públicamente luego de la denuncia realizada por thelma fardín.“defendí en su momento a una persona en la que confiaba mucho. lo consideraba un amigo (…). en su momento pensé que calu estaba confundida por las incomodidades de una escena", manifestó la actriz. “pero luego me fui enterando de otras cosas, de mujeres que sufrieron situaciones similares, hasta que me enteré lo de thelma y la llamé. hablando por teléfono con thelma me puse a llorar, se me rompió el corazón. porque esa no era la persona que yo conocí, sentí una decepción enorme, y se me vino encima la responsabilidad de haber defendido públicamente a la persona incorrecta. ahí pedí mis disculpas en privado y luego públicamente”, escribió eva. .
👉más info en haceinstantes.com
.

text:
everybody goes through ups and downs in their lives. they manifest what they believe and they believe what they’re taught. i obviously am very analytic and detail-oriented while also very, very emotional and empathetic.
i wasn’t deprived, malnourished, locked in my room and ignored. i had what i needed growing up and am grateful. but i looked so far into everything because i didn’t understand. i was/am obsessed with why people did/do such bad things, how people can be so selfish, why others are unable to empathize with the ones they “love”, and why it’s so hard to listen to someone with your full attention.
i experienced quite a bit of traumatic experiences in a short time, and wasn’t able to come to terms with it (and become who i am today) until years later. what i want to do is create a blog. i want to share my run-on thoughts, my doodles, my story, my favorite quotes, my interpretations of things. i want to help others, even if it’s just by assisting them in finding a new way to look at things. i want to show people that i may not have been in the exact same situations but i’m willing to mentally put myself there or look back on a situation i have been in to relate and offer the advice and affirmations i wish i’d had.
who would follow me once i create a website and all that? or who would help me make one? if i have the opportunity to help somebody feel valued, appreciated, understood and loved by getting personal and being transparent and vulnerable, i’ll do it.
i feel that i can inspire others to love themselves regardless of where they fall in today’s standards and expectations.
@selflovewithsam gets credit for this quote on her story highlights! super touched and inspired by her which is why i was compelled to share today.❤️
contact me whenever, however. i’m open to any advice or support, per usual!

text:
#miracomonosponemos 
no se trata de quien haga la denuncia, ni cuando, para estas historias el tiempo no pasa.
(hay que hacerla al fin) 
no se trata del color del pañuelo
🌺
no se trata de si estás de acuerdo con el modo. 
con la forma. 
con el hashtag. 
no nos importa la bandera política.
🌺
es más simple
🌺
tiene que ver con que todos sepamos que 
no es no. 
y también tiene que ver con la posibilidad de que una mujer, tú hermana, hija sobrina amiga (u hombre porque no) camine sola por las calles sin sentir ese miedo que ya naturalizamos.
🌺
basta del “piropo” desubicado en la calle, del silbido, de los ojos desviados. de la apoyada innecesaria.
basta de la tocada de culo en el bondi o en el boliche. de la agresión innecesaria.
qué les pasa ?
🌺
está en casa mejorarnos a nosotros mismos, explicar a los mayores que crecieron y hasta se acostumbraron con este pensamiento y forma.
está en casa inculcar a los menores, de como tratarse, del respeto perdido, de valores básicos, de los límites que siempre existieron y que fueron saltados.
🌺
hay mucho por decir, charlar, debatir y aún más por hacer pero de a poco se avanza.
🌺
y sobretodo hay que amar más.
.
.
.
#noesno #bastaya #metoo #miracomonosponemos

そういえば帰りの飛行機の中で後ろの席の最初から嫌な予感がしたんやけど奇声を発していて『死ね』とか『自殺しろ』とか色々言ってて寝れなくて『静かにして下さい』って自分で言ったりしてたら(キャビンさんにも言って貰った)頭を殴られた。
もちろん航空警察にも行った。

text:
hace un tiempo inicio el movimiento #metoo en ee.uu y el mundo se sorprendió. 
mujeres, que uno veía en una pantalla y las creía más allá de todo esto, sufrían lo mismo que nosotras. acoso, degradación, violencia...por el simple hecho de ser mujer y estar (supuestamente)un escalón por debajo de los hombres.
ayer, actrices argentinas, ponen en marcha el #miracomonosponemos. 
es necesario preguntar cómo estabas vestida? si estabas sola? porqué te pusiste en esa situación? decir "ella se lo busco"?
las estadísticas son terribles pero nos damos el lujo de hablar de feminazis, marimachos y cientos de adjetivos más que no nos ayudan a ver lo que en verdad está pasando.
#metoo significa que a mí también me pasó, que yo también estuve en esa situación, que yo también un día tuve que cruzar de vereda o volver a mi casa con miedo, que yo sentí que era menos por ser mujer.
soy madre de un hijo varón y tía de tres sobrinas adorables, mi desafío es que mi hijo crezca apreciando, valorando y respetando a las mujeres en todas las formas posibles. y que mis sobrinas no tengan que ser valientes para crecer en una sociedad que no las respete si no que crezcan siendo libres.
porque a mi también me paso pero mira como nos ponemos hoy!

text:
🇪🇸 no exageramos cuando decimos que nos ha pasado a casi todas. faltas de respeto, abusos, agresiones sexuales o violación. 
procesar el daño y el dolor lleva tiempo. las mujeres (y hombres) que sienten que pueden, hablan. y aún en ese momento, quizás 20 años después, el miedo sigue siendo paralizante. porque no nos creen, porque dudan de nuestros testimonios, porque nos preguntan qué habremos hecho, porque la vergüenza sigue siendo nuestra (!), porque la “justicia” nunca responde. 
que sirva para ser voz de las que aún no pueden. que sirva para que nos crean a todxs. que sirva como ejemplo de que se está cayendo. 
#yositecreo, siempre. 
#miracomonosponemos #nonoscallamosmas #hermanayositecreo #seestacayendo
.
.
.
.
🇬🇧 yesterday a group of argentinean actrices gathered to denounce the rape of one of them when she was 16 by hands of another argentinean (very famous) actor, 45 at the time. this criminal and social sue strengthens the strong female movement that started two years ago here in argentina. 
we don’t exaggerate when we say it had happened to most of us. rudeness, abuse, sexual aggression or rape. 
it takes time to process the damage & pain. those who feel like they can, talk. and even then, maybe 20 years later, fear can be paralyzing. because they don’t believe us, they doubt our testimonies, they ask what were we wearing, because the shame is somehow still ours (!), because “justice” always fails us. 
hoping these movements, social claims and demands be the voice of those who still can’t speak up. open eyes and heads so that they start believing us. be the proof that patriarchy is falling. 
#ibelieveyou, i always do. 
#starttheconversation #believesurvivors #metoo #ibelieveher

with a strong belief in yourself, your value and your worth, there is nothing to stop you from building the life you truly deserve!

text:
posted on december 11, 2018 3:20pm

a stay-at-home mom of three is firing back after a judge allegedly “verbally assaulted” her “for mothering [her] children.” in a facebook post shared on nov. 21 that has since gone viral, fresno, california-based christa pehl evans recalled an incident the previous day that took place at the fresno superior courthouse, when judge james petrucelli would not allow her to be exempt from jury duty to take care of her kids. “when i asked to be excused because i need to care for my children, these are things judge james petrucelli (dept. 61, fresno superior courthouse) said to me,” wrote pehl evans, who is mom to son harvey, 5, plus daughters sylvia, 16 months, and violet, 7.

she went on to allege that she had been on the receiving end of comments from petrucelli such as, “i don’t care about your children” and “who is going to take care of your children when you get hit by a mack truck?” pehl evans continued, ” ‘what do you do when you are sick?’ i replied, ‘i take care of my kids,’ and he shook his head at me with a disgusted expression on his face.” ” ‘what do you do when you have to do something?’ ” she claimed of another line of questioning. “i replied, ‘i take my baby.’ ”

want all the latest pregnancy and birth announcements, plus celebrity mom blogs? click here to get those and more in the people parents newsletter. “and then, obviously directed at me and the other very pregnant mother of a 20 month old: ‘i just don’t understand these people with no childcare,’ ” pehl evans alleged, stating that the conversation “went on and on in front of the entire courtroom.” (according to the court transcript, the sacramento bee reports, petrucelli’s statement was, “i’m amazed that people don’t have childcare available to them.”) “there were almost 300 people at the courthouse called to serve jury duty, and judge james petrucelli chose to berate two mothers of young children,” she went on. “in contrast the man in the room asking to get off the jury because he needed money from his job to support his family was not questioned. judge petrucelli simply nodded his head in agreement with him.”
name: California Libertarian

text:
desde ayer estoy tratando de poner en palabras todo el dolor que siento con todo lo que está pasando, solo se me ocurren dos; que desolador y triste vivir en un país donde, encubren violadores, hacen responsable a la víctima de lo qué pasó, donde todos los días liberan a femicidas y abusadores, crean un show de una violación, nos empalan, nos secuestran, nos violan, nos pegan, nos torturan, nos matan. 
dejen de darles espacio en los medios a estos seres nefastos, dejen de justificarlos, dejen de tratar de entenderlos, dejen de defenderlos. el tiempo de impunidad para los abusadores tienen que terminar. todas fuimos acosadas alguna vez, desde que nacemos somos obligadas a naturalizar cosas que no deberíamos naturalizar, por esto, no dudes del testimonio de una piba, ninguna es libre si nuestra compañera no lo es, abracemos a la piba que tenemos al lado, acompañémosla, querámosla, ayudémosla, comprendámosla y creámosle.
estábamos calladas porque teníamos miedo, pero ahora, no, ahora gritamos, con ganas, porque estamos cansadas, enojadas, porque estamos hartas.

text:
great day, great story ❤️ perfect fit for a #1000thpost 😊 
last week i had a meeting at dance4life @dance4lifenl ❤️ this dutch non-profit organization is committed to providing young people worldwide the knowledge, skills and trust to make healthy sexual choices. in their journey4life-program they train young people with a sex education using the universal language of dance and the positive energy of music. once they become trainers they start teaching the program to other youngsters in their country of origin. such a lovely initiative! and so very helpful in reducing the numbers of sexual violence, aids, unwanted pregnancy.. i’m so very thankful to inform you that i’m joining them on their journey and will be donating my love, time, energy and money as of january 2019. even though 2018 isn’t over yet.. i already know it has taken me home 🙏 #careforothers loving evening everyone ❤️
name: Yvonne | Philanthropist ❤️

text_retweet:
amen! nothing to add but the white ribbon🎗to all written below by @unclerush  by the way white ribbon campaign is the largest in the world male initiative against all forms of violence and discrimination towards women  #repost ・・・
i still whole heartedly support #metoo despite my experiences  it is already tremendously successful  and i believe its time for all men to support the rise of the divine feminine especially in cultural and governmental affairs. we need more nurturing and thoughtful leadership  in these powerful positions... hollywood is where social justice and other issues travel  so it makes sense that they should lead it  and i applaud the women doing the work. as for me i have been a playboy all my life i accept that the new more accurate term for playboy is womanizer  therefore i accept that i have been part of the problem  and i’m here now to be part of the solution  hollywood is a great place to brand an idea and it has been tremendously helpful in pointing out where we as a society need lots of work  however hollywood is also the place where money and fame are sought after the most ... in every great revolution there is some collateral damage  i am sad  for the many men who are being extorted or unjustly accused (and there are many)  but  it is worth it if my daughters will live in a world where the agenda for women is advanced  i am fearful left that without a shift to balance this current wave of unconscious masculine leadership, we as a species could be fucked... the future must be more brown, (inclusive) ..more conscious ,and more feminine ❤️

text:
hoy no es posible hablar de otra cosa. lo qué pasó ayer es una sacudida enorme para todos esos que todavía no abrieron los ojos a una realidad que vivimos, en mayor o menor medida, todas las mujeres de este país. el abuso no es “normal”, no son “cosas que pasan”, no lo naturalices, no te acostumbres, no lo escondas, el abuso es abuso. si lo viviste o lo estás viviendo, no te calles, si lo estas escuchando, no lo minimices. hablar, escuchar, apoyar. es importante seguir diciéndolo hasta que todo el mundo lo entienda y lo respete, no es no. no importa quién sea, dónde estés o cómo estás vestida, en cualquier circunstancia no es no.

no nos callamos más. si sufriste cualquier situación de abuso o violencia llamá al 144 o al 137. mirá como nos ponemos 💪🏻 #noesno #miracomonosponemos #nonoscallamosmas #metoo #feminism

text:
yes we can! it's easy to let doubts and fears hold us back. remember your voice has power. you can change things. if there's no seat for you at the table, bring your own. "and i think that's a problem with us as women — we don't think we need to be in the power structure, that we need to be on those boards where decisions are being made. sometimes we think well, i'm not really prepared to take that position or that role. but i say [to women out there]: just do it like the guys do it — pretend that you know. and then you learn on the job." -- dolores huerta

text:
ayer leí la noticia de la violación de thelma ferdín. me hierve la sangre de enojo de saber su caso, pero me deja una profunda tristeza leer los comentarios de hombres y mujeres que consideran que “está buscando publicidad”, “necesita reactivar su carrera”, “sólo busca dinero”, o cuestionan estúpidamente “¿porqué espero tantos años para denunciar?” lo mismo ocurrió cuando comenzó el movimiento #metoo y sobre todo cuando karla souza hizo público su caso.
aquella ocasión no escribí nada, me concreté a expresar mis opiniones con quienes convivo cara a cara, pero creo que es tiempo que alguien lo escriba por acá. 
si ustedes nunca han sido víctimas de una agresión sexual, me da mucho gusto, pero considero que eso los limita a expresar una opinión, pues es algo que nunca han vivido. 
quienes hemos sido “nalgueadas” en la calle, a las que nos han metido a la fuerza a un local abandonado y jaloneado la blusa y manoseado mientras las inmovilizan con su cuerpo; a las que nos han llevado lejos en una camioneta y se han salvado de una violación porque accedieron a dar “un beso”; las que tuvimos “un novio” manipulador que encubría con “amor” el abuso, sabemos porqué callamos.
y les hablo desde mi experiencia: callamos porque nos sentimos usadas, sucias, humilladas cuando nos tocan sin nuestro consentimiento; a algunas la agresión “nos bloquea” para gritar porque no sabes si para callarte te van a meter un navajazo o porque el cuerpo de ellos es tan pesado que no te deja aire para gritar, en otras ocasiones el abusador es tan labioso que te manipula lo suficiente para que creas que es amor lo que vives y cuando sales de esa “relación”, después de curar mucho y madurar otro tanto te das cuenta que lo que vivías eran agresiones físicas, psicológicas y sexuales que no decías y no denunciabas porque todo es tan natural, que tú crees que es normal. 
sigue en comentarios

text:
saying peace to the girl i used to be. ⁣
⁣
stepping into the woman i’m destined to be. ⁣
⁣
saying peace to the unrealistic expectations i’ve put on myself. ⁣
⁣
saying hello to the whisper of my soul and following its lead. ⁣
⁣
saying peace to the “control” i’ve been grasping onto so tightly for almost 35 years. ⁣
⁣
welcoming the slow & intentional flow of life, second by second. ⁣
⁣
saying peace to the tight shallow breathing that once suffocated me. ⁣
⁣
pursuing the deep thoughtful breaths that fill me with life. ⁣
⁣
saying peace to the fear of judgment from others. ⁣
⁣
unapologetically being who and what i’m meant to be without hesitation. ⁣
⁣
saying peace to anything that doesn’t serve my soul’s purpose.⁣
⁣
inviting all of the love, light, peace and healing into every part of my being. ⁣
⁣
✨💗🦏🙏🏻⁣
⁣
what do you need to say, “peace” to my dear? ⁣
perhaps, it’s time...⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
.⁣
.⁣
.⁣
.⁣
.⁣
.⁣
.⁣
.⁣

text_retweet:
kindly let me know when my story get posted.
this story is not really about me but about my parents. i think my mom and dad would have done their self a whole lot of good if they had never gotten married in the first place, from what we heard while growing up, both of them were match made by their parents hence that might be the reason they never loved each other. it's always from one fight to the other, the violence in our house is just too much, most times my dad is at fault but mom also does not know when to keep quiet, i hear the noise from my mom, the beatings, the hitting.... it's always one bruise or the other for my mom and i see it all despite the tons of makeup that covers it up, i'm 17 right now and i've seen it all and i can honestly say it's better having two happy separated parents than two miserable individuals that has refused to do themselves and the society a ton of good  by going on their separate ways all for the sake of flimsy excuses. i've advised my mom several times to go for divorce but guess she says? there has never been an history of divorce in her family so it can't start with her, also stones she says it's all because of us(her children) but i would feel a lot better if they're separated cause i'm scared that one day they would have a fight and she won't come out alive.  thanks for creating this platform @shareurxprience cause i've been looking for an avenue to let it all out for a while.

text:

. the fact that you push forward when things try to hold you back is rewarding. it shows character. you are stronger than you know and once you look back and see what you have been through... you will see just how much you can handle. but don’t let that continue. you may have tolerated enough... now it’s time to step forward. make a stand and keep pressing forward. just because you fought through the pain does not mean you have to continue to live in it. walk through fire... but keep walking with the flames that carry your soul in strength and wisdom. .
.
.

text:
personal update💞
the big moments in your life are made up by the little decisions you make.

i personally didn't make a big decision to get into an abusive relationship. i made a little decision to lower my integrity bar. i made another little decision to stay, when i saw the first signs that he didn't honor me the way i deserve to be honored. losing yourself over a someone who is lost is one of the worst things you could do to yourself.

it was my job to fall madly in love with myself first so i could set the example for others how to love me. 
you are the first example what loving you looks like and the way you love you is the way the world is going to love you. 
i'm here to incurage those who battle with whatever it is you're battling with to come forward and seek the help you need to feel better🍀 
there's no reason for use to keep suffering in silence because the world is not ready for some real talk. 
so here's your friendly reminder to press reset today. it's never to late to fall madly in love with yourself first💕

no more shame!!!! xoxo #keep_it_happyhealth

text:
:
ok let’s get it out in the open. :
:

sexual harassment is serious and it happens, whether you choose to acknowledge it or not.  how do you picture it happening? the perpetrator dragging the victim by the hair and satisfying their lust? :
:

no. :
:

it’s mostly done, away from prying eyes. :
:

so please don’t snigger, gossip, make fun off the situation. victims come forward because it gives them a closure. it might take the victim years to actually do it. they are aware it’s their word against the perpetrators’. still it gives them a voice, confidence to speak up. :
:

boys be aware of the rules. if she is friend zoning you, take it as a no. she doesn’t want to sleep with you. end off. and if she has said no to you, you stfu and go away. and i know men get harassed and raped too. #mentoo
:
:

and there’s no such thing as ‘she was asking for it’! no. walking around without wearing a bullet proof jacket is not asking to be shot in the chest!?
:
:  if you have experienced sexual harassment talk about it openly. tell everyone. doesn’t matter who believes you. you are the victim not the cause! there’s no shame. hope others raise aware of this serious issue as well. #influencer. in support of the #metoo movement. •

text_retweet:
#repost @malenagalmarini
• • • • •
y un día todo se rompe.
la ilusión, la inocencia, la sonrisa, la confianza.
un día todo lo rompe.
necesita demostrar, alardear y ejecer su poder.
y te “elige”. y todo lo rompe.

y tu vida cambia.
te sentís sucia, te sentís culpable, te sentís rota.
y te embarga la angustia, el mundo se llena de soledad, todo se aleja. 
y parece una película. le pasa a otra. no sos vos. y así seguís. tiempo, mucho tiempo. eterno e interminable tiempo.

y un día todo aparece; de nuevo.
sin pedir permiso, vuelve.
y el miedo te gana. y te ahogan las lágrimas. 
y la confianza está rota. 
y querés que te crean. y querés que te abracen (pero te sentís sucia). y todos hablan. y nadie escucha. y quién te cree?

hasta que un día juntás los pedazos. y un día alguien te junta los pedazos. y todo se pega. y te da la mano y te acompaña al camino. y no te empuja.

y encontrás una pequeña confianza. nueva. suave. luminosa. y te animás.
y nadie habla. y todos escuchan. y alguien te cree.
y empezás sanar. 
sólo necesitan escuchar; sólo necesitamos respeto. #noesno

#nielprimeronielúltimonielúnico

#yotecreo
#miracomonosponemos
#metoo
#niunamenos
#bastadeviolencia
#sevaacaerolovamosatirar

text:
100% yes!
.
while we need people who can come forward and share their trauma stories for a host of reasons, we also must make sure there is plenty of space for the countless folks who can't. that is the beauty in #metoo in its original creation. it was a safe way to find reciprocity. .
in order to find healing in sharing you need many conditions to be met and many people don't have those resources in place. one thing i love about my work is that it does not need narrative. .

text:
read what raquel has to say about what is actually taking place in an ista training. she took part in the level 1 training both as a participant and an assistant.

what is ista level 1? for outsiders

disclaimer - this is based on my experience, and everyone's experience is unique, because it's a deep process!

i first came across ista totally by chance; i was travelling with my beloved in guatemala and a poster caught my attention. probably because it had the word sex in it, and because it looked attractive and exotic. david and i signed up as a present to our love, not knowing what the week would be about. we are both grateful we took the plunge, as ista l1 is a well-oiled machine!

so why are people so mysterious about ista level 1? why can't they just give me the curriculum so i can decide if it's for me? the answer is simple; a lot of the transformational work that is done during that week needs to be in context. out of context it sounds nuts. i have done 2 level 1, once as a participant, and another time as an assistant, and i can guarantee that my learning and journey was unique each time. however, i understand that your mind wants something more palpable, so here goes.
in one sentence - ista level 1 is the education every human being should get when growing up.

boundaries - do you ever feel like you should have said no, but ended up saying yes? this relates to #metoo, but it also relates to those times when you accept too much responsibility at work, when you give a friend a shoulder although you really don't have the emotional strength at that moment, and other situations in which you are not clear about your boundaries and end up feeling depleted. ista level 1 explores this expertly from different angles, so even if you think you are brilliant with your boundaries (and the boundaries of others), you'll become better.

tools - even if you are content and emotionally switched on, there is space to become happier, more connected to your feelings, desires, fears, dreams…

read the full article on our facebook page facebook.com/awakemeditation/

or follow the link in our bio for more info on ista in portugal 
#tantra #istatribe #transformational #retreat

text:
another story of a young woman's experience with sexual assault.  this teen boy felt entitled to her body, which is why rape and rape culture continues....
"it was summer between ninth and tenth grade. my friends and i went to this boy's house. they had known him since grade school, but i had only met him that year. it was the middle of the day so his parents were at work. there were a bunch of us drinking and horsing around. some of my friends started to disappear into other rooms with their boyfriends or boys they liked. i remained in the den with the guy whose house it was. he eventually tried to kiss me and before i knew it, his hands were all over me. i was trying to push him off and he got even more determined. he got angry and began to fuss about how i liked other boys and how he was just as good as them. i was drunk and scared. the others heard the scuffle and came in and pulled him off of me. my friends and i left and from that day on i never saw him the same. i knew he was dangerous and i knew exactly what he was capable of." #childsexabuseawareness #stopchildsexabuse #childsexabusesurvivor #parentsofchilldsexabusesurvivor #sexualassault #endchildsexabuse #endrapeculture #childabuse #sextrafficking #atlanta #atl #georgia #women #girls #teens #awareness #rapevictim #victim #children #prevention #trafficking  #survivor #tips #blogger #speaker #metoo #advocate

text:
ahora que sí nos ven
(texto y gráfica de villy)

estamos siendo parte de un cambio profundo hoy, ya, ahora y urgente. un cambio por y para nosotras, pero sobre todo para todas esas mujeres que vendrán, para que el futuro las encuentre leyendo sobre patriarcado en los libros de historia y que esos mismos libros digan que luchamos y que no estuvimos de acuerdo. porque en hechos está demostrado que en la injusticia crece nuestro grito, en un crecimiento sostenido e indestructible. y ya no tenemos miedo porque sabemos que no estamos solas, que por cada golpe nos vamos a levantar mas fuertes que antes. estamos unidas por el deseo ardiente de cambiarlo todo. 
así que con los ojos bien abiertos mira el presente y el futuro que se viene, ¿querés ver cómo nos ponemos?. fuertes. libres. juntas.
.
.
.
.

text:
outside the matrix 101: the weaponization of music

if you want to find the secrets of the universe, think in terms of energy, frequency and vibration.

god created the universe using sound, yah spoke and it was.

what i find amazing is how i am drawn to songs in 432 and how those songs give you chills or brings you to tears. when you listen to old vinyls you can feel the music in your soul. on a cd or mp3 you can only hear the music. many of bob marley's classics were made in 432hz, they have switched all modern songs to 440hz and worse.

i listened to the carpenters album in both frequencies. when i listened to the 440 hz, it felt like i was on edge or edgy and slightly off-centered in some way. then when i listened to the 432, it felt like sitting in a chair that was totally conformed to my body and felt centered, relaxed and peaceful.

the reason the wrong frequency is so dangerous to us is because we are mostly composed of water. look at the effects on water and understand that your body is made up of 60% water. music can change the frequency in your body. it changes the mood and energy instantly.

every sound in nature travels by wavelength. that wavelength is determined by frequency and amplitude. frequency is the actual pitch you hear. so, 440 or 432 refers to the frequency of the sound wave of the actual pitches that would be played in a scale. just like you can have a scale that starts on "c" or "c#" or "d" or any note you choose, modes start on whatever note you choose and then the pattern of half steps and whole steps between the pitches are what make a mode what it is.

432 is a vibration humans vibrate at peacefully. tesla's theory frequency vibration resonance. nothing happens ever without these three things happening. simple terms frequency= electricity, vibrations=vibrations, resonance =heat. we live in electric universe.

440 became the standard in the 1940's, after the information was discovered by the nazis and then spread globally after the war. the nazis scientist were imported into the west.

it's amazing how they have weaponized every single thing that reaches us through our senses.

per favore, usiamo i social in modo diverso, almeno ogni tanto. 
è ora di parlare, è ora di dire no.

text:
the plea deal of former baylor frat president jacob anderson on 4 charges of sexual assault is like a punch in the stomach to me as a survivor.
.
earlier this week, before this news broke, i told my counselor - "one of the hardest things for me is people who aren't outraged when someone is sexually assaulted."
.
for a perpetrator to sexually assault someone they have to dehumanize the victim to a certain extent. i believe the same is true when rulings such as this are issued. something else is put above the survivor, above this horrendous crime, above protecting future potential victims of this perpetrator.
.
on september 26, i was driving in my car when i heard the news of bill cosby's sentencing, and i cried. i cried because i know how hard to is for a survivor to come forward. i know how hard it is to get the police to charge your offender. i cried because not all cases that go to court result in a conviction. it was not just a victory for andrea constad, but also for every other survivor of bill cosby's crimes, and for every other #metoo survivor in the world. although 3 to 10 years doesn't even begin to match the punishment deserved, i cried tears of gratitude because that day one survivor had some amount of justice.
.
what happened to you is evil. nothing and no one's opinion lesson the truth of that. if you decide to report, and no charges are made - if it does go to court but there isn't a conviction - if there is a conviction, but the sentencing is like a slap in the face . . . none of that changes the truth that what happened to you is an atrocity.
.
what happened to you is horrendous. what happened to you is not your fault. surround yourself with people who do believe you. your story matters. you matter. keep fighting for yourself every day, you are worth more than you realize.
.
#believesurvivors #nomore #ibelieveyou #yourstorymatters #youmatter #timesup #keepfighting #andreaconstand #billcosby #jacobanderson #jacobwalteranderson #sexualassault #survivors #icwlh
