text:
cuando era chica sufrí reiterados abusos por parte de alguien de mi entorno. durante años.
amenazas, difamación.
sentí y siento vergüenza, bronca, tristeza y miedo, mucho miedo. 
tardè años en ser consciente del verdadero dñao3 que eso me había hecho a muchos niveles.
no fue hasta el año pasado que fui capaz de hablarlo con mis padres y algunas personas más. no es fácil verbalizar y revivir esa mierda.
mi mayor miedo era que me culparan, que no me creyeran. hoy, con 33 años y 2 hijas me sigo sintiendo igual. me da pánico ser juzgada, porque esa persona hizo bien su trabajo y consiguió que en esa época se tuviese una imagen de mi que estaba muy lejos de la realidad. 
debería y querria poder enfrentarme a esa persona y preguntarle porque me cagó la vida de esa manera... espero algún día ser capaz de hacerlo. por mi, por mis hijas y por todas las chicas y chicos que sufren del acoso, el abuso, la violacion etc.
quiero que mis hijas crezcan más libres y valientes. que ellas sí sean capaces de poner nombre y apellido a quien pueda cometer un abuso del tipo que sea. y, sobre todo, que encuentren en su mamá y en su papá esa figura protectora y de apoyo que se necesita.
pero lo que más deseo es que ni ellas ni nadie tenga que vivir una situación de esa índole
#nonoscallanmas #miracomonosponemos #metoo #yotecreohermana

text:
el actor argentino #juandarthés, a quien la actriz #thelmafardín ha denunciado por violación, aseguró hoy que dicha acusación “es una locura” y “no es verdad” y pidió esperar “los tiempos” de la justicia.

este martes, fardín, rodeada de multitud de actrices argentinas, reveló en una conferencia de prensa que presentó una denuncia en nicaragua contra darthés, al que acusa de haberla violado en 2009, cuando ella tenía 16 años y estaban en una gira en ese país con la novela “patito feo”. “una noche comenzó a besarme el cuello, y yo le dije que no. me agarró la mano, hizo que lo tocara y me dijo ‘mirá como me ponés’, haciéndome sentir su erección. yo seguía diciendo que no”, afirmó fardín en un video divulgado de forma previa al encuentro de prensa con el colectivo actrices argentinas, que aglutina a más de 400 profesionales del espectáculo.

según fardín, cuando sucedió el abuso, ella tenía 16 años y él 45 y él era el único adulto del grupo de intérpretes. el hecho ha conmocionado a argentina entera, y los medios de comunicación locales están ahondando en un asunto que según las actrices no ha hecho sino empezar y puede convertirse en el #metoo argentino, en alusión al escándalo iniciado en hollywood en 2017, cuando el productor harvey weinstein fue acusado de haber abusado de multitud de mujeres de la industria del cine. 
#mirácómonosponemos, gritaron las actrices argentinas durante la rueda de prensa, un lema que ya se ha hecho popular en las redes sociales. darthés ya había sido acusado de abuso sexual el año pasado por la argentina calu rivero y a ella se sumaron las también actrices anita coacci y natalia juncos. sin embargo, hasta ahora la justicia no ha avanzado contra el artista. (lee más en www.hoy.com.do) #periódicohoy

text:
christopher wylie, the whistleblower who exposed the widespread misuse of data by his former employer, cambridge analytica, has revealed how the company “weaponised” the fashion industry in the run up to the 2016 us election, which he claims helped donald trump get elected.

speaking at the annual bof voices festival in oxfordshire, wylie revealed for the first time a matrix based on data collected by the firm which he claims can show how users’ preferences for particular brands on social media platforms – facebook, in particular – were then used to help target these same users with pro-trump messaging. he compared the misuse of fashion-based data as one of the campaign’s lesser reported “weapons of mass destruction”. - they [cambridge analytica] looked at actual people. how they engaged with certain brands was put into a funnel and helped build the algorithms, wylie explained. - when you look at personality traits, music and fashion are the most informative [tools] for predicting someone’s personality. a user’s predilection for a particular label gives, he said, a very clear indication of what reports often call “populist political signalling”. cambridge analytica, which was shut down earlier this year following an investigation by the observer, was the political marketing firm headed by trump’s former key adviser, steve bannon, and owned by hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. it also used user information obtained without authorisation in early 2014 – including cultural preferences such as fashion and music – to create a system that could single out voters in order to expose them to specific political advertising.

morwenna ferrier
the guardian

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

for me, feeling beautiful inside and out played a huge part in my healing journey. it's all about how you feel and often how you take care of yourself. i believe that beauty comes from within. confidence, your personal energy, and aura go hand-in-hand. while physical health is most easily seen with the naked eye, mental and emotional trauma associated with not liking what you see in the mirror is very real. many don’t discuss it for fear of feeling vain. don’t be hard on yourself for desiring to look and feel your best—moving forward with real confidence is where change starts.
.

let's talk, research and find a way to deal with domestic violence in a just manner that has true accountability.

text: there’s no such thing as white privilege they say... ————————————-look at this video. now imagine yourself, your mother, your sister or your child being raped and beat repeatedly by a grown man. imagine the fear. imagine the self worth he stole. imagine feeling hopeless. imagine feeling like your body is not your body, but belongs to the man beating you. imagine not being able to say no to sexual favors. ——————————————— can you imagine that? not yet? well imagine someone inserting their penis into your vagina (anus for men) and due to it not being warranted, there’s no lubrications to help the pain. you feel every rip and tear caused by the insertion... get it now?! —————————————————-a rape is not only about sex! it is emotionally damaging, and severely mentally damaging. when you’re raped, you remember the smallest details like the scent of the rapist breath. or that they had a bump on their hand. this is diagnosed as ptsd. you’ll deal with some form of ptsd for life!!!!! so to be sentenced to life, for trying to save your life from a person continuously rapes you of everything is a double slap in the face. then to know a guy who raped a woman gets off scott free?!!!!! what the hell is out justice system for if justice is only for a small group of people?!?! please call the number listed. i’m going to invest my time and effort to help free cyntoia. from one survivor to another, you deserve your life back. #cyntoiabrown #bianquahunter #metoo #rainn #theshaderoom #madamnoire #sexualassault #awareness #justice #survivor

text:
"el primer paso para acabar con el sufrimiento es que nuestra integridad física, nuestros cuerpos, nuestras mentes y nuestros corazones sean respetados siempre y en todo lugar. las mujeres tenemos que luchar por nuestra credibilidad, esa que el poder judicial, los medios, las instituciones o los valores, por defecto, nos niegan. no nos creen, ni como victimas ni como testigos, ni en los centros de estudio o de trabajo...no es casualidad; el patriarcado convierte a las mujeres en seres heridos, lastimados, llenas de miedo y de culpa, sumisas, masoquistas, adictas a las relaciones toxicas, a sobrevivir en un espiral permanente de autocritica y de critica a las demás mujeres, a las que nos enseñan a ver como enemigas y competidoras."
"hay un paso esencial en la vida de toda mujer, un paso que marca un antes y un después, un paso que cambiara tu vida, tu pensamiento y tu acción: el momento en el que sales de la mentalidad masculina que nos impregna y comienzas a sentir y a pensar desde ti como mujer que desea ser libre, desde un nosotras como casta oprimida en lucha por la libertad, pero este paso puede ser revertido. a nuestro pesar seguimos viviendo en una sociedad patriarcal que constantemente trata de devolvernos a su "normalidad", sea mediante amenazas, persecución o asesinatos...si queremos vivir con un mínimo de libertad y dignidad, hemos de estrechar lazos con otras mujeres y luchar juntas por la liberación. a las mujeres no se nos regala nada; hemos de luchar o morir asesinadas."
#nonoscallamosmas #miracomonosponemos  #noesno #metoo #sevacaer
name: Helbert Natasha
tweet_full:
"el primer paso para acabar con el sufrimiento es que nuestra integridad física, nuestros cuerpos, nuestras mentes y nuestros corazones sean respetados siempre y en todo lugar. las mujeres tenemos que luchar por nuestra credibilidad, esa que el poder judicial, los medios, las instituciones o los valores, por defecto, nos niegan. no nos creen, ni como victimas ni como testigos, ni en los centros de estudio o de trabajo...no es casualidad; el patriarcado convierte a las mujeres en seres heridos, lastimados, llenas de miedo y de culpa, sumisas, masoquistas, adictas a las relaciones toxicas, a sobrevivir en un espiral permanente de autocritica y de critica a las demás mujeres, a las que nos enseñan a ver como enemigas y competidoras."
"hay un paso esencial en la vida de toda mujer, un paso que marca un antes y un después, un paso que cambiara tu vida, tu pensamiento y tu acción: el momento en el que sales de la mentalidad masculina que nos impregna y comienzas a sentir y a pensar desde ti como mujer que desea ser libre, desde un nosotras como casta oprimida en lucha por la libertad, pero este paso puede ser revertido. a nuestro pesar seguimos viviendo en una sociedad patriarcal que constantemente trata de devolvernos a su "normalidad", sea mediante amenazas, persecución o asesinatos...si queremos vivir con un mínimo de libertad y dignidad, hemos de estrechar lazos con otras mujeres y luchar juntas por la liberación. a las mujeres no se nos regala nada; hemos de luchar o morir asesinadas."
#nonoscallamosmas #miracomonosponemos  #noesno #metoo #sevacaer

text:
(reuters) - attorneys for bill cosby outlined their grounds on tuesday for appealing his sexual assault conviction, citing what they called errors in legal procedure that may have biased the jury and warrant a new trial for the once-beloved comedian. the 81-year-old performer, best known for his role as the lovable family man and physician on the hit television sitcom “the cosby show,” was found guilty by a pennsylvania jury in april of drugging and sexually assaulting a onetime friend in 2004.

it marked the first such criminal conviction of a celebrity accused of sexual misconduct since the #metoo movement that has brought down dozens of powerful, privileged men in american media, politics and business since the autumn of 2017.

in september, the trial judge, steven o’neill, designated cosby a “sexually violent predator” under pennsylvania law, requiring the entertainer to register as a sex offender for life, and sentenced him to a term of three to 10 years in prison.

cosby, who is married, has insisted all along that any sexual encounters he had were consensual. he was found guilty on three counts of aggravated indecent assault.

in an eight-page filing laying out the basis of their appeal, cosby’s lawyers focused on several instances they said introduced bias into the trial, including the judge’s refusal to excuse a juror that the defense argued was unable to be fair and impartial. #freebillcosby #farfromfinished #justice #corruption #thecosbyshow #blackexcellence #wronglyconvicted #billcosby

text:
matt lauer accused of sexual harassment by multiple women: as the co-host of nbc’s “today,” matt lauer once gave a colleague a sex toy as a present. it included an explicit note about how he wanted to use it on her, which left her mortified.

on another day, he summoned a different female employee to his office, and then dropped his pants, showing her his penis. after the employee declined to do anything, visibly shaken, he reprimanded her for not engaging in a sexual act. these accounts of lauer’s behavior at nbc are the result of a two-month investigation by variety, with dozens of interviews with current and former staffers. variety has talked to three women who identified themselves as victims of sexual harassment by lauer, and their stories have been corroborated by friends or colleagues that they told at the time. they have asked for now to remain unnamed, fearing professional repercussions.
 #metoo

text_retweet:
throwback to our first article -  how we began one year ago today 👓 🎂  one can dream…⁣
⁣
donald trump has resigned today as a result of the multiple sexual assault allegations.⁣
⁣
“i’m sorry that my actions have hurt so many.  i’m sorry for being a bad role model for today’s youth.” —donald trump⁣
⁣
the latest in the wave of #metoo casualties, his resignation comes as the latest fallout in a series of high profile resignations.⁣
⁣
after dismissing such allegations during his historic funnel hack of the 2016 us presidential elections, he finally came to a breakthrough when he saw a mother with her baby in an adoring crowd.  the baby wore a bib covered in spittle that said make america great again.  as trump approached the baby to kiss it, he saw a look of fright in her eyes.  a look he’d recognized over 20 times before in the eyes of his accusers.⁣
⁣
at that point his whereabouts became unknown, even to the secret service.  some say he visited the statue of lincoln.  others thought they’d saw him visiting a series of taco trucks in southern new mexico.⁣
⁣
when he finally emerged back onto twitter at 3am, it was with a simple tweet, one of only a handful of characters: #meetoo.  he then deleted that tweet hours later and followed up with a second tweet: #metoo.⁣
⁣
in a dramatic turn of events, he fired vice president mike pence and appointed political activist and former black panther angela davis as his new vice president.⁣
⁣
he then abruptly retired.  on his way out, he left one final tweet: i just made america great again.⁣
⁣
⁣

text:
cuando calu rivero denunció a darthes por acoso sexual, eva de dominici no le creyo, porque no podía creer que su amigo fuera un abusador. 
ahora, eva se disculpa, bancando a thelma y escrachando a darthes como el abusador que es, porque se dio cuenta que su amigo también es un macho de mierda. 
vos, también tenés un abusador en tu familia, en tu grupo de amigxs, tus compañerxs de escuela/facultad/ trabajo a los que les bancas los "micro"machismos, los abusos a otras pibas, porque no las conoces y seguro son unas regaladas que algo habrán hecho para provocar. 
rescatate amigue, aborta al macho que hay en vos y al que tenés al lado.

el "siempre con las pibas" es siempre con las pibas. que no se te lo olvide cuando tenés un vínculo con el abusador. 
mira como nos ponemos, juntas, empoderadas, armadas, hermanadas y en manada, lo vamos a tirar a la mierda🔥

somos las brujas, somos el fuego, ahora que ardan ellos 🔥

#miracomonosponemos #yanonoscallamosmas #yositecreo #metoo #yotambien #niunamenos #vivasylibres #vivasnosqueremos

text:
looking out on a grey sky ready to attend a meeting to decide my future... feeling so anxious, out of control & completely emotional.. 😐🙄😥 am i technically 'incapable' of performing my duties as a teacher for the foreseeable future???? 😑😶🙄 that seems to have already been decided... but what to do with me now???🤷‍♀️ i have fought so hard to get where i am...something that i have always been ridiculed for by my family..."your such a disaster, why do you make everything so difficult, you'll never manage that!"☢ 🤔😶🙄😥😪😟😭🚫👨‍👩‍👧‍👦 yes, it took me about 7 years to complete my first masters degree (after i escaped from unbearable hell at home age 16) i worked 3 jobs, suffered great personal loss, including bereavement, domestic violence, rape, narcisstic & emotional abuse. i sacrificed my needs for family & friends & i did it with adhd, crippling anxiety, agoraphobia, depression, bpd & other mental health problems & crap i hid from the world (& myself)😶🙄🤨 but...i got through it...maybe just, but... i survived...💪🤞👊 i also managed to travel the world, fit in marriage, buy a house then complete another degree for a full career change before i was 30! but its only today that i can actually admit these things happened to me! good & bad! i can feel the pain & deal with it... but i am also learning i can be proud of my achievements & actually they mean more after accepting what i have had to overcome 😊

it's only now... when i'm faced with everything being taken away from me, that i can see...im not 'bad' or 'hard work'... i am human😐 i am flawed, beaten but not broken😀😉☺💪 i am determined...i will not let anyone else control the outcome of my life with doubts, lies or pain💔🤞❤ *so scared to post this!! hate being so vulnerable & honest but without this we cant make change!

#mentalsonthemove
#mentalhealthadvocate #mentalhealthstigma

text:
it was alone in my bed that i first knew. my mind looped over and over what he did. in the quiet darkness with no escape and no distractions i finally listened.
my stomach felt sick as my mind replayed each time he raped me. it’s three years later an instead of sleeping my brain still tells me the same nightmare.
i can say i’m fine.
i can breathe and take my meds.
i can journal and exercise and tell myself the truth.
but at night it all comes back.
too tired to reason with myself, i experience it all again, and again, and again.
i just want to sleep.
but i cannot.
i cannot forget the way his voice sounds.
i cannot forget the way he slept beside me.
i cannot forget the way his body felt against mine.
i cannot unlove him, and it’s killing me.
(1/9) •
•
•
•
•
•

text:
episode 27 is #live. in this installment of #tbkow that #goodbrothers go full hard on everyone. no seriously, we legit shit on everyone. were we cranky? probably. were we a wee bit tired? yes. was it a long week? absolutely. but in our defense, everyone needs to quit being so damn #offended.

also during this episode we have an open discuss on the kareem hunt controversy and discuss whether or not the woman should take a bit of the blame (don’t worry, we think violence towards women is repugnant), give our thoughts on the kevin hart stepping down from hosting the sinking ship that is the oscar’s, look into the neil tyson degrasse sexual assault/misconduct allegations, absolutely shit on florida driver’s, applaud an irish mother who sent her child to school with blow up sheep that actually was a sex doll, and look into a 2017 report of two facebook chatbot’s (robots) that developed a language that only they could understand.

the music heard this week was “another year” by darren campbell. you can follow him on the gram @darrencampbellmusic. you can also visit him on the interwebs at https://darrencampbell.bandcamp.com.

the sponsor this week was @foundersbrewing all day ipa.

text:
as part of our migration month, we’re exploring the specific ways in which women are uniquely affected by the crossing of borders. such crossings are often violent, exploitative and coercive. according to the united nations, women account for 71 percent of trafficking victims, with sexual exploitation being the most common type.
.
the international organisation for migration estimated that between 2014 and 2016, that victims of trafficking arriving in italy increased 600 percent. open migration explore further the journey that nigerian women who are trafficked into scilly face:
.
"the first stage of the process is “recruiting”: the girl is approached by a friend, relative, or someone she trusts who offers to help her reach europe and put her in touch with other people. “this proposal aims to lure girls in extremely poor living conditions. sometimes they are perfectly aware of what awaits them, but they consider it a better perspective,” trovato says. in larger families, it is often the elder daughters who undertake this journey to help their relatives. unfortunately, most of the time, the victim has no idea of what will happen: somebody tricks her by talking about a friend who is looking for a shop assistant, hair-plaiter, or babysitter in italy." - claudia torrisi .
.
@openmigration
.

.

text:
"yo le dije que no, que no y él siguió"
tras la presentación de la denuncia por violación contra el actor, fardin dio su testimonio a página/12. cuando ocurrió el hecho durante una gira de patito feo en nicaragua ella tenía 16 años.
 mira como me pones --me dice - y me hace que lo toque.  yo le digo que no, le digo que no. el sigue". no. no. no. ella lo repitió. no. no. no. ella tenía 16 años. y denunció que el actor juan darthes, de 45 años entonces, se abalanzó sobre su cuerpo, en un hotel en nicaragua, en el último día de la gira latinoamericana de la serie infanto juvenil "patito feo" que se emitió en canal 13. y ahora, nueve años después, en consonancia con un grito colectivo que va desde ni una menos al repudio por el fallo machista en la muerte de lucía pérez, logró ir a managua y ser escuchada ante la justicia. 
el 8 de diciembre la embajada argentina en managua certificó la denuncia de la actriz thelma fardin ante el ministerio público de nicaragua realizada el 4 de diciembre. se remitió una copia al ministerio de relaciones exteriores y culto de la argentina que es mucho más que un documento burocrático. es un símbolo de la sororidad y la decisión de no callar más de una actriz y de un colectivo feminista que une lazos en argentina y latinoamérica y que busca desbloquear de la mutilación del silencio a las víctimas. pero, además, reflejar que los modos de producción de la televisión no pueden seguir mirando a otro canal cuando son protagonizadas y miradas por niñas, niños y adolescentes. 
thelma tiene ahora 26 años e ingresó al elenco de "patito feo" cuando tenía 14 años. trabajo desde el verano del 2007 hasta mayo del 2009 en el papel de josefina. allí se produjo una situación que logró, con el apoyo de organizaciones feministas, de derechos humanos y de la colectiva actrices argentinas, denunciar en la justicia de nicaragua. el silencio no se rompe solo, sino con un movimiento feminista que alza la voz. por eso, el relato no se vuelve fragmento, sino parte de un rompecabezas de las formas de ejercer y mostrar la impunidad del machismo, en medio de un éxito que volvió a una de sus protagonistas vulnerable #femins #mujereslibres #yodecido #metoo

text:
my ptsd has been acting up lately. i don’t talk about it. ever. if i do talk about it, it’s a very skimmed version to let others know #metoo isn’t just a stupid movement. i don’t talk about my 2 molestations. or the almost rape that happened. i don’t talk about them. it physically makes me ill to do it. my mom knows more than anyone but still i don’t tell her the details. 
recently i was told, for my health, i need to talk about it. instant answer was nope, ain’t doing it. i was already told once that a person doesn’t believe me, so why put myself there again? but i need to. #molestationandrapeawareness is important. i’m a #molestationsurvivor and i’m ok with that fact. i don’t want anyone else to have to suffer the mental pain from this. so i’ll talk. once. to those that need to hear. but that’s all i’m doing.

text:
recomendaciones | navidades libres de #asi 🎄 
1.- si dejas a tus hijos en casa de un familiar, elabora un plan de monitoreo, explicando a qué horas vas a llamarlos durante el día. habla con sus cuidadores de la importancia que le das a las decisiones de tus hijos. 
2.- al inscribir a tus hijos en planes vacacionales o campamentos, solicitalos criterios y protocolos de seguridad bajo los que estarán tus hijos, así como las formas de comunicación que se pueden tener durante sus paseos.

3.- recuérdale a tus hijos que su cuerpo les pertenece, que todos tenemos partes que son visibles y partes que son privadas. las partes privadas: pene, vulva, nalgas y las semiprivadas: boca y pecho no deben sermostradas ni tocadas.

text: 25 was arguably the worst/best year of my life. going through multiple assaults (couple different kinds, ya, #metoo ), moving 8 times, going through the worst battle yet with depression and anxiety, a few suicide attempts, and several more bridges burned.. i used to wake up every day and wonder why tf i'm still here when so many amazing people have died.. yet i persevered. i'm blessed to see 26. ik now that because of everything that's happened to me, i'm stronger than i've ever been and improving every day. i've stopped focusing on my losses. i've stopped dwelling on the past and wondering what could've been. my eyes are set dead straight on my goals and i'm never going back to that broken being i was. i've been trying to avoid another big post filled with big empty promises but this is different. i've learned it ain't about the l, it's about the come up. and mine is gonna be legendary, believe that 💯

text:
🇦🇷les pregunté a mis amigas si alguna vez vivieron este tipo de acoso callejero, o peor, si algún tipo alguna vez se masturbó en frente de ellas. todas menos una me dijeron que sí.

algunas lo vivimos a los 10 años. sí, ¡a los 10 años! íbamos caminando una siesta y empieza a seguirnos un tipo en una bici. de repente frena, saca el pene afuera y empieza a masturbarse. 
y acá reitero lo que me comentó @mi_regazo en el post anterior: incluso cuando no decimos que no, es no. ¿lo naturalizamos? ¿o lo enfrentamos?

hoy se lo conté a mi papá. hoy me entendió porqué una mujer jamás es ‘provocativa’. hoy me entendió porqué estoy tan metida en la lucha de mis derechos, los de mis sobrinas y de todas las generaciones que vienen detrás.

no nos callamos más.

basta. 🇺🇸i asked my friends if they’ve ever faced street harrassment in their lives. unluckily, all but one answered yes. some of us faced it when we were 10 years old. we were walking by the street when we were approached by a man who started to masturbate. 
today i told about this to my dad. now he understands that women are never provocative.

we won’t keep quiet any more. #metoo

"it’s easy to think that good guys finish last and bullies get ahead “when we see a few prominent examples that dominate the conversation,” says porath, a former conference speaker, in her new tedx talk. but ultimately, she says, bad guys end up sabotaging themselves…we’re still wowed bynew york times report, “#metoo brought down 201 men. nearly half of their replacements are women.”… in this fast company article, where fashion company owners rebecca minkoff and sarah lafleur ask and answer each other’s questions, we were struck by the format—and their candor…. speaking of women entrepreneurs, we can’t get enough of new podcast “pretty electric,” with dynamic duo dara kaplan and gwenwunderlich (there are 16 episodes, last time we checked.)"

tengo mucho orgullo de tener vos como mi idola euge ❤

#repost @clarincom (@get_repost)
・・・
#mirácómonosponemos

es el mensaje de miles de mujeres en las redes sociales que se unieron para apoyar la causa de la actriz @soythelmafardin, quien denunció por violación a juan darthés durante una gira que compartieron por la tira “patito feo”.
en una conferencia de prensa realizada junto al colectivo @actrices.argentinas, la joven contó en detalle cómo y cuándo ocurrieron los hechos: "me dijo que si yo accedía, me iba a garantizar trabajo. le dije que no y él siguió", fueron algunas de sus palabras que se escucharon con potencia.
pese al dolor, las muestras de apoyo fueron inmediatas. no solo de las colegas que le sostuvieron la mano en el escenario, como @griseldasiciliani, @lolafonca, @soyjazminstuart, @laliespositoo, @lauraazcurra y @lacalurivero, otra denunciante de darthés. también, lo hicieron a la distancia excompañeras de la novela juvenil como @basnicar y, además, @sangrejaponesa que pidió perdón públicamente por dichos del pasado. en cuanto a @ana.rosenfeld la abogada finalmente expuso porqué dejó la defensa del actor #metoo #metooargentina #niunamenos #pañueloverde

text:
2018:
*
"the takeaway of harvey weinstein’s recent i’ve-had-one-hell-of-year e-mail could easily apply to the fashion industry, too."
*
"while the year started with media reports of bombshell allegations of sexual misconduct and abuse against major league photographers, plenty of other firestorms erupted in the months that followed. reports of overly handsy executives, a dearth of non-slender models on the runway, victoria secret’s alarmingly non-#metoo-fashion show and dolce & gabbana’s public apology for offensive instagram posts against the chinese were just some of the fiery issues that seared the fashion crowd throughout 2018."
*
"the need for greater diversity permeated on many levels — runway shows, advertising shoots, c-suites, women’s empowerment and in editorial. from start to finish, there were calls for more diversity, inclusivity and respect. building from the momentum first sparked by last year’s women’s march and the groundswell of support for the #metoo and time’s up movements, women and people of all persuasions increasingly voiced their opinion."
*
"after published reports of alleged sexual abuse, kering and lvmh moët hennessy louis vuitton issued a charter for models in the fall of 2017, and then condé nast and tapestry inc. — parent of coach and kate spade — released ones of their own for photo/video shoots and fashion shows and presentations with the intention of safeguarding those who work with the companies. the cfda emphasized the importance of creating a safe environment, asking designers, show producers and photographers to consider using venues for shoots and runway shows that have areas where models can change in privacy."
*
"in may, 100 models banded together to create a program to try to end sexual harassment in the fashion industry. led by the model alliance’s founder sara ziff, the new “respect” program asks brands, modeling agencies and media outlets to sign a legally binding agreement to protect models."
*
absolutely incredible year in the #businessofmodeling as countless #socialinnovator #fashionmodels emerged with their initiatives and ventures."
*
#futureofmodels #futureofwork 
#fashiothon

text:
yo te creo! 
yo te creo, claro que te creo. a vos y a todas las que desde las vísceras, desde el alma, desde las entrañas, desde los años sufridos, desde la vergüenza, desde el honor mutilado tienen algo por decir y por denunciar. 
yo te creo, porque desde la amenaza, el miedo, la vergüenza, el asco, el sentir que "algo habrán hecho" ,puede algún canalla suelto, (que son muchos pero son los menos),:
desde la manipulación pueden con una que sufre, que se asusta, que es gigante pero se siente chiquita.
pero sin duda, no pueden los canallas,no pueden con tod@s, no pueden con las voces que se levantan, no pueden con oídos que escuchan, no pueden con una historia que tendría que haber cambiado hace mucho pero está cambiando ahora, 
y digo , digo desde el cuero y desde el cuore, ¡yo te creo!
nunca más te calles, nunca más pienses que te lo mereces, nunca más , no es no, tu cuerpo es tuyo y nadie puede rozarte siquiera si vos decís que no. 
contá conmigo,y con muchos más, no estas sola.
"tu no puedes volver atrás, porque la vida ya te empuja como un aullido interminable, interminable..."
yo te creo...
#yotecreo #miracomonosponemos #niunamenos #metoo #basta.  ale schujman

text:
#provinciales tras la denuncia de thelma fardin, sacan a juan darthés de un festival de tango en #olta
el actor, acusado de violar a su compañera de patito feo cuando era menor, iba a cantar el 20 de diciembre en olta.
la organización del festival de tango "caminito", que se realizará el 20 de diciembre en la rioja, excluyó hoy de la grilla del evento al actor y cantante juan darthés.
la decisión de sacarlo a darthés la tomaron luego que el martes el colectivo actrices argentinas comunicara la denuncia por violación en su contra que le realizó la actriz thelma fardin en nicaragua.
"caminito" es un festival de tango destinado a reivindicar, promocionar y fomentar el patrimonio histórico-cultural que representa el tango del mismo nombre.
el predio donde se realiza el festival, en la localidad riojana de olta, del departamento general belgrano, a comienzos del siglo xx fue testigo del amor entre dos jóvenes, uno de cuyos protagonistas, gabino coria peñaloza, convirtió en versos para darle la letra al célebre tango que musicalizó juan de dios filiberto.
el evento contará con la presencia de numerosos cantantes y bailarines nacionales y locales, entre los que se encontraba darthés, a quien se buscará reemplazar por otro artista, entre los que se barajan néstor fabián y adriana varela, según informó télam.
fuente: web diario clarín 
sitio www.chepesrvp.com.ar #larioja #chepesrvp #metoo

text: ternion: 16 x 16 in, acrylic on canvas. ternion is a grouping of three. i’ve been thinking a lot about relationships lately. with so many changes happening in so many lives, politics encroaching every aspect of our conversations and the seasonal stress of the holidays, our collective souls have lost a bit of empathy with strangers... and friends. as much as we are different, we are all the same. the trinity here is: you, me and the space we share. i could speak of family, shed some light on the elephant in the room for those that think they know my situation. i could write about my post the other day remembering a shot of tequila with a politician that’s got his eye on the presidential election of 2020 and the vitriol that erupted for no reason. i could talk about the weekend of festiveness shared with my grandmother and a friend, which would’ve been fun to share with others as well. but, instead, i’ll talk about you and me and the circle we share. it isn’t the space between that drives us apart; it’s the space together that’s shared without respect that hurts us all. i’ve always loved circles, the symbology of an everlasting embrace. by posting my paintings and writing a bit about them, i’m inviting you into my space. by looking at this, you are entering my circle to create another. it’s a simply understood allegory. but, also, we do this everyday from buying a cold drink at 7-11 and the exchange with the cashier, holding the door at the mall to help someone with their hands full to tapping a heart on instagram or commenting on a fb post. in this crazy world with so many layers of color and chaos, it’s easy to forget every interaction we have with another is over lapping our circle, creating new ones which effect people’s lives in big and small ways. this is that reflection. #livingwithart #jennifire #circleoflife #attitudeofgratitude #happinessishere #wednesdaywisdom #seasonsgreetings #mindfulness #acrylicpainting #embrace #metoo #spraydaily #simplelife  #womenartists #dallasart #glasslife #weareone #respectyourself #oprahsbookclub #respectlife #strongertogether #artlove  #womenwriters #meditation #plur #plurlife #blessup #soulshine #lovequotes #lifelesson

text: l'attrice argentina thelma fardin (giusy nella serie), conosciuta per aver preso parte alla serie tv "il mondo di patty", ha denunciato un collega attore, juan darthés (leandro padre di patty nella serie), accusandolo di averla violentata in nicaragua nel 2009, quando lei aveva 16 anni e lui 45. darthes era il promotore della serie, interpretata da giovani aspiranti attrici minorenni. le parole di fardin hanno suscitato immediatamente la solidarietà dell'associazione attrici argentine e oltre 100 donne che ne fanno parte si sono fatte fotografare con lei, in un gesto che oggi è sulle prime pagine di molti giornali a buenos aires. darthes ha negato i fatti, scrivendo su twitter: "è pazzesco, non è mai successo nulla". fardin ha spiegato di essersi convinta a parlare grazie al movimento niunamenos, versione argentina del #metoo di hollywood: ha trovato il coraggio di denunciare durante una conferenza stampa in un teatro della capitale argentina, mostrando un video molto forte, in cui tra le lacrime racconta i dettagli del presunto stupro, poi condiviso anche su instagram.

text:
how do we improve the workplace for disabled employees?
mencap’s #hereiam campaign identifies “there are 1.4 million people in the uk with a learning disability”, yet “just 6% of people with a learning disability known to social services are in paid employment”.
we need to ensure our workplaces offer a supportive and inclusive environment for disabled employees.
employers have a duty to make reasonable adjustments to ensure disabled employee can carry out their role – particularly if the current place, practice or procedure of an organisation unfairly disadvantages an employee with a disability. it is important to note here that employers who do not adhere to their duty to provide reasonable adjustments risk discriminating against disabled employees.
reasonable adjustments may include allocated parking spaces closer to the office building, a desk with adjustable height, allowing for regular breaks, offering flexible working or providing an employee with a mentor.
so how do we ensure we provide this supportive environment where reasonable adjustments can be made? by opening up the conversation and asking disabled employees how they can be supported to help them fulfil their role – asking, rather than assuming, or worse, box ticking!  #gurls #workplace #woman #entrepreneur #femaleentrepreneur

text:
📣 “yo tenía 16 años. él tenía 45. se subió encima de mí y yo le dije que no” 📣

la intérprete de “patito feo”, thelma fardín, se une al movimiento #metoo argentino y ha denunciado a través de un video la violación que sufrío cuando tenía 16 años. el presunto agresor es el actor juan darthé y los hechos narrados por fardín ocurrieron en 2009 cuando ambos estaban de gira con el exitoso programa infantil. 
la denuncia de la actriz está presentada en nicaragua, lugar donde ocurrieron los hechos, y será la justicia del país caribeño la que se ocupe del caso. 📷 thelma fardín

text:
#hiddenapronradio episode 031: the new filipino kitchen authors pt. 2 east coast edition - featuring katrina and kristine villavicencio - co-creators of the d.c. supper club @timpladc. also featuring alexa alfaro - owner of @meatonthestreet
•
expectations. expectations around filipino food (looks, tastes, methods, and costs). expectations around our age and the need to balance respectful obedience and forging our own path. expectations around the immigrant experience and the constant theme of sacrifice. expectations around gender; something we don’t get to cover much on this show. i’m glad we talked about this topic in the wake of the #metoo movement and the fortuity that a majority of the co-authors i’ve been touring with and are getting the much-deserved spotlight (seeing as immigrant women are the keepers of cuisine) are female.
•
of note to me was how we can think about our relationships with women in and out of the kitchen, and where we draw the line between demanding excellence at work and abuse.
•

text:
hey folks. the past week i’ve been inpatient. instead of planning for finals last week i planned my death. it was such a weird place to be in my head. recent events triggered my ptsd and it spiraled out of control honestly. i stopped eating, thinking that my body was trying to kill me anyways, might as well help it along. i stopped drinking water and got awful headaches and cramps. one of my friends left my life(which i was okay with) but it didn’t help my already poor health. 
my heart would pound out of my chest from the time i woke up to the time i fell asleep. i wanted to do it without medicine, which was stupid because now that i’m medicated, my heart beats a lot closer to normal. my friends i thought would be better off without me actually care and i still get to take my finals, so my hard work won’t be for nothing like i thought. i was knocked down but i’m not out for the count yet. it feels all too personal, but i never want anyone to feel this way, to feel so alone and misunderstood. please reach out if you feel like suicide is your only option. i love you, please stay strong. 
#ptsd#womenempowerment#anxiety#depression#survivor#metoo#keepitreal#onedayatatime#mentalhealth#womenarestrong#littlefighter#bigdreamer

text:
where, after all, do universal human rights begin? in small places, close to home -- so close and so small that they cannot be seen on any maps of the world. [...] unless these rights have meaning there, they have little meaning anywhere. without concerted citizen action to uphold them close to home, we shall look in vain for progress in the larger world." -- eleanor roosevelt
teaching young girls their rights is the first step to preventing or reducing abuse, because when is aware she reports to the right  channel when she sees or experiences other wise, and in doing so we are reducing the cases of abuse and the number of broken adults due to abusive childhood in the society.

text:
the #metoo from argentina. 
under the hashtag #miracomonosponemos, more than 500 argentine actresses gave a press conference yesterday to support the rape complaint of actress thelma fardin against actor juan darthés when she was 16 y/o. yesterday,  9 years later, fardin spoke out so others can hear her too. #argentina has been at the forefront of latin america in some of the feminist claims. in this country was born, in 2015, the movement #niunamenos against #femicides that later was replicated in the rest of the continent. in 2017 they organized the first women's strike in the region and this year was marked by the collective struggle for the legalization of #abortion, which was finally stopped in the senate and authorized only in some cases. in south america, only uruguay allows women to freely decide on the interruption of their pregnancy. link in bio. #miracomonosponemos #thelmafardin #metoo #womensrights #genderviolence #actricesargentinas

text:
✨même si mon compte permet de découvrir la france... je suis une femme et je ne peux pas rester insensible à ce qui se passe. .
💪🏻le mouvement #metoo initié par des actrices aux états unis et en france forme maintenant une vague en argentine. .
✨hier, plus de 50 actrices argentines se sont réunies pour dire stop au harcèlement et à l’abus sexuel! .
.
💪🏻étant en ce moment à buenos aires, je peux partager de prêt la solidarité qui se reflète par les réseaux sociaux.
.
✨non c’est non! 
ensemble, nous sommes plus!.
.
. ✨si bien mi cuenta se refiere a que conozcamos más francia...soy mujer y no puedo ser ajena a esto que está sucediendo.
.
💪🏻el movimiento #metoo que impulsaron actrices de los estados unidos y francia, ahora deja huella en la argentina. .
✨en el día de ayer más de 50 actrices argentinas se unieron para decir basta con el acoso y abuso sexual!.
.
💪🏻justo me toca estar en este momento en buenos aires y poder compartir desde cerca esta solidaridad que se reflejó en las redes sociales.
.
✨no es no! juntas somos más! ❤️
.
.
.
#miracomonosponemos #noesno #basta #expatriadas #ciudadanasdelmundo #sonorité #fraternité

text: this story is called: 1 train, 30 minutes and 2 men. today on my way to work i almost missed the train. luckily for me, the driver open again the door so i got in and even got enough time to hold the door for a 50+ year old man behind me. i sit down and 7 stops later a young guy gets on the train with a banana on one hand and a painting on the other. he suddenly asked me ‘do you want a banana?’ i prepared myself to say no thank you and he added ‘the banana in my pants’. i told him not to do that shit ever again to any women and try to make him understand why what he said was disrespectful. he couldn’t care less - he said i clearly have gone through some shit and that’s why i didn’t appreciate his comment (aren’t we all women went through a kid of this stupid shit?!) - i thought to myself ok at least is daytime and if i need help i’m sure the old guy will help me. wrong! the train stopped at my station i got up - the old guy got up and gave me this note... i guess dave is also not a safe guy to go to! as a souvenir, i got a banana in my purse and a note from old creep dave in my fist. feel free to show dave some love: 6466707717. #metoo #showdavesomelove

text:
mercury re-enters sagittarius .
.

mercury is moving forwards, crossing back into the flashing lights of #sagittarius tonight, on december 12, where they began their retrograde journey on november 16. sagittarius is the sign of the guru, prophet, or priest; ruled by #jupiter, who wants to bring justice, but who’s mythology is a mixture of good and ill behavior. it is fitting then that as mercury worked their way out of #scorpio--jupiter in scorpio brought us the #metoo movement--towards sag, sexual abuse allegations emerged against a popular spiritual healer, john of god, in brazil. .
.

more and more people are seeking spiritual solutions to the big issues facing our world, but, inevitably, as we go deeper into this arena, and as spiritual practices expand, we encounter abuse of power. the curative powers of john of god are world renowned. how disillusioning then, that the individual could be harmful when the energy flowing through him was healing. it is hard to square this, but mercury in sagittarius will not look away. the winged messenger delivers the truth whether we want it, or are ready for it, or not. this dispersing fire energy will be with us for the remainder of the year, causing our minds to dash and dart this way and that. it’s not the most serene feeling. mercury in sag likes to get up on a high horse, but they are also seeking the small, tangible solution to the larger spiritual problem. .
.

what can each of us do today to #believewomen and support survivors? one tangible step is to call to tennessee governor bill haslam urging him to grant clemency to #cyntoiabrown a survivor of sex trafficking who was sentenced to 51 years for murdering her abuser. we can contrast her case with brock turner’s lenient sentence of 6 months for rape to understand the unjust consequences of racial and gender bias in the legal system. .
.

mercury is moving into a conjunction with jupiter that will perfect on the #wintersolistice. as we move towards the longest night, may each of us be small beacons lighting the way for each other as we travel the path towards death and rebirth. 
#astrology #queerastrology #freecyntoia #endrape

text:
new class to zenon: fundamental improvisation/contact improvisation taught by taja will. for our winter/spring session, sundays 2-3:30pm!
@tajawillxo 
photo: nanne sorvold
.

this class will focus on the intersections of structured improvisation, somatic modalities and contact improvisation skills. structured improvisation will serve to inform our body's connections to elements such as space, time, geometry and range. somatic modalities serve to inform our embodied relationship to ourselves, anatomical intelligence, our choices and how they echo within a space. contact improvisation will be the vehicle for movement that seeks relationship, textures of touch and our consent to be in dialogue with a partner or ensemble.
.

as a fundamental part of my pedagogy i employ a restorative justice lens to these ways of moving. i am interested in using language that acknowledges systems of power, privilege and the historical marginalization of individuals who are bipoc, queer, non-binary, trans, and artists with disabilities. 
in the era of #metoo i am committed to boldly transparent consent in touch based dance forms. 
it is my intention to develop this awareness in every class for bolder, safer spaces of inclusion. - taja will diversity & inclusion consultant & facilitator
.

taja will is a queer, chilean adoptee, performer, choreographer, therapist and restorative justice facilitator. her approach integrates improvisation, somatic modalities, text and vocals in contemporary  performance. will’s aesthetic is one of spontaneity, bold choice making, sonic and kinetic partnership and the ability to move in relationship to risk and intimacy.  she explores visceral connections to current socio-cultural realities through archetypes and everyday magic.
.
.
.
.

#fundamentalimprovisation #fundamentalcontactimprovisation #improvisation #contactimprovisation #learnimprovisation #learncontactimprovisation #improv #newclass #tajawill #dance #zenondance #wewillmoveyou

text:
el arte cuando ya no podes más 
el arte cuando no podes hablar
y entonces hablas.
y hablar se vuelve arte.
el arte mas revolucionario, mas estremecedor. 
no callar mas
¿que esto es un circo? eso dicen.
¿de qué se sorprenden? pan y circo hubo desde siempre.
y si esto también es un circo, de este circo sí quiero ser parte.
porque no cosifica, no lava cerebros ni entretiene.
este circo visibiliza, interpela. 
este circo se llama feminismo y está tirando al patriarcado.
habla. hablemos.
te hacemos el espacio. nos hacemos el espacio.
hermana yo te juro que te creo. así, a ciegas y sin pruebas, sin necesidad de que me cuentes detalles, te creo. prefiero quedar como idiota si al final me mentis, que quedar como complice por creerle a un violador. 
sí, hablar hoy es un arte. y el arte es un transformador social.
y hablar hoy es nuestra revolucion mas grande.
no nos callamos mas.

no es no.
te lo digo a vos.
me lo digo a mí. 
se lo digo al sistema patriarcal 
no es no.

text:
thelma fardin ha denunciado al también actor argentino juan darthés, por haberla violado cuando ella tenía 16 años y él 45. era el único adulto que viajaba con ella en una gira de exitoso programa infantil. fardin le ha denunciado diez años después, cuando otras artistas ya lo habían hecho. muchos han criticado su forma de maquillarse o de editar el vídeo en el que explica su experiencia con darthés, cómo le reiteró que ella no quería, le recordó que tenía hijes de su edad... la respuesta del actor: "mirá cómo me ponés". .
por esto el colectivo feminista en argentina ha inundado las redes sociales con mensajes de apoyo a thelma con #mirácómonosponemos que acompaña al #nonoscallamosmás que además sirve para continuar mostrando la indignación y repulsa ante la absolución de los violadores y asesinos de lucía pérez, también de16 años. ¿ser rico y famoso significa ser intocable ante la justicia?
.

text:
tools for releasing 🙏🏼✨
.
if you read my last post you’ll know a little bit about what helped me release negative energy after my sexual assault. (if you haven’t read the last post - giirrlll, go read that first!) 💁🏼‍♀️
.
the thing about trauma or any kind of negative experience is that it isn’t just surface level.
.
negative energy, trauma, and deep physical or emotional pain all go deep into our soul and into the core of our being!
.
think about it like this: imagine you just spilled red wine on your shirt. in order to make sure it doesn’t stain you need to clean it asap.
.
but what if you don’t clean it immediately... or what if you clean it a bit but miss a spot?!
.
the wine will sink into the microfibres of the shirt. it seeps in and has time to soak up there... becoming way more nestled and habituated!
.
there is still a chance you can get the stain out, but now it’s going to take more time, energy, and effort because it started to become part of the fibre. it’s no longer separate... it’s like it’s become a natural part of the clothing!
.
this is exactly the same thing when it comes to deep pain. most of us release a little bit and then bottle it up. we hide it from others and try to forget about it, hoping it will just disappear with time! but the longer we hold onto it the deeper rooted it becomes, and the more engrained and permanent it seems.
.
i truly believe in a holistic and well-rounded approach to release these things. i don’t think there is a one-size-fits-all model, because we are unique and everyone has different experiences and beliefs that need to be accounted for.
.
but here are some examples of different methods i’ve used on myself or with my clients:
-meditation
-energy healing (like reiki)
-inner child and shadow work
-clearing subconscious patterning
-mindset shifts
-neurolinguistic programming
-chakra balancing
-tibetan heart yoga
... among others!
.
but aside from those, what is most important is creating a safe space to dive headfirst into these issues. we cannot continue to push them aside if we want to truly heal and release the negative energy or limiting patterns that surround them! 💕

text:
i want you to repeat after me and i'll be repeating this to myself as well: "taking care of myself doesn't mean 'me first,' it means 'me too!"' we take care of others, especially the ones we love, and that's a wonderful quality and a kind way to be, yet we need to remember to include ourselves in that "taking care of" process.

taking care of yourself isn't selfish or putting yourself first, although there are times you need to put yourself first, especially when you're feeling drained, tired or exhausted. you're of no use to anyone unless you're well rested, healthy and balanced. and you know that.

so, today i want you to remind yourself that you're not saying "me first" by taking care of yourself, you're simply including yourself in taking care of others by saying "me too." and that is a good thing! <3

wishing you love and light, ~anne dennish~

#metoo #takingcareofyourself #takingcareofothers #balance #loveyourself #anne_dennish #wakingup #quotes

text:
@hidden_apron #hiddenapronradio episode 031: the new filipino kitchen authors pt. 2 east coast edition - featuring katrina and kristine villavicencio - co-creators of the d.c. supper club @timpladc. also featuring alexa alfaro - owner of @meatonthestreet
•
expectations. expectations around filipino food (looks, tastes, methods, and costs). expectations around our age and the need to balance respectful obedience and forging our own path. expectations around the immigrant experience and the constant theme of sacrifice. expectations around gender; something we don’t get to cover much on this show. i’m glad we talked about this topic in the wake of the #metoo movement and the fortuity that a majority of the co-authors i’ve been touring with and are getting the much-deserved spotlight (seeing as immigrant women are the keepers of cuisine) are female.
•
of note to me was how we can think about our relationships with women in and out of the kitchen, and where we draw the line between demanding excellence at work and abuse.
•
link in bio. download. share. enjoy🎙#gastro #theerrantdiner #foodpodcast #podcast

text:
"in waco, texas, a former baylor student charged with rape was given a plea deal that never even came close to giving justice to the victim. we've heard this story before, with brock turner.
🚫
judges are making lenient plea deals for men charged with crimes like rape, creating a culture where the severity of the consequence is less than the severity of the action. it's time to stop. 🚫
what about the women who have to watch their attacker walk the streets, having received nothing more slap on the wrist? it is absolute inequality, as well as ludicrous. this baylor victim in particular has expressed outrage as well as exhaustion with the broken justice system. and rightly so. it’s time to stop making the punishment of such a severe crime literally nothing. it’s time to stop letting college men get away with rape."
🚫

text:
keep up the pressure! let @governorbillhaslam know that we demand clemency for cyntoia!
.
 #governorhaslam was speaking at an event on the importance of higher education in #tennessee on monday when justin laing, a member of #blacklivesmatter #nashville, stepped up to the mic during the audience question portion.
.
.
“since we’re here talking about education, i wanted to ask a question about one of your tennessee students and a graduate of #lipscombuniversity, cyntoia brown,” laing said, to audience applause. "as a victim of sex trafficking and assault, this is an unjust sentence in the first place,” laing said. .
.
under tennessee law, all minors engaged in #sexwork are legally considered victims of sex trafficking. .
.
“she has not been treated as a victim of trafficking and not given the justice she deserves,” laing said. “and so i ask you, what really, functionally, is the difference between life without parole and ‘you might get parole after 51 years,’ for a victim of sex trafficking? why has #cyntoiabrown been incarcerated for 14 years for enduring harm? and so i say governor haslam, you have the power and ability to grant clemency to cyntoia brown, how will you answer to this human rights violation that the state of tennessee is committing by keeping her incarcerated?”
.
.
the governor thanked laing for his question, and responded
“we’re reviewing a lot of cases,” he said, “and while #cyntoia’s case has gotten a lot of publicity, i don’t think you want us to treat hers any different than a whole lot of cases that i think people want us to review.”
.
.
governor haslam reiterated that his office is talking to everyone involved in brown’s case, will have a decision on clemency before he leaves office in six weeks. .
.

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
this struck a chord. when someone tried to make me feel small, i doubled back even bigger. 💁🏻‍♀️
.
.
.

to that “leader” who talked down to me, i wore taller heels. .
.
.
to the man who thought they could get away with some #metoo shit, turns out you messed with the wrong 25 year old. your harvey weinstein fall from grace will come. (ps your lucky my husband respected my request to let me confront you instead of him🥊)
.
.
.
to the people that unfairly judge, criticize or bully others, you must be a sad person. you only made me want to be kinder to the next. .
.
.
get bigger. when you feel someone trying to make you small, make yourself bigger, stronger, grittier (is that a word?!). #rachelhollis #girlstopapologizing #girlwashyourface #getbigger #grow #empower #choosekind

⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

text:
for years i spoke pro bono, refusing to receive $$, because the simple thought of sharing my story and getting paid made me feel as though i was exploiting it. it took me a number of years and a handful of mentors to help me realize that my story has value and that to accept compensation gave me the rare opportunity (not right) to have a far greater reach. now, not only do i get paid to do work that i’m incredibly proud of, but i also have the ability to continually invest further in my speaking career.
•
speaking into people’s lives...it’s a privilege and not one i take lightly. unfortunately, the more i’ve ventured into the world of professional speaking, the more i’ve realized that there are countless speakers out there who are merely speaking to be heard & seen, rather than to see & hear. countless speakers who measure their worth by the # of gigs they get, the amount of followers (not relationships) they have, and the amount of $$ in their bank accounts.
•
it breaks my heart that audiences act surprised when i stay after events to offer love, support and guidance to anyone who needs it. surprised that instead of collecting my paycheck and darting for the door, i make it a priority to take the time to personally pour into them. and surprised that i provide my personal phone number at each event and offer calls to anyone who just needs a listening ear.
•
it breaks my heart. that as a society we’ve gotten to a place where we prioritize our “hustle” for
fame
exposure
&
“success”
- o v e r -
empathy and connection.
•
as speakers, we’re supposed to be helping others to shine light in their darkness, not selfishly and greedily stealing the light for ourselves.
•
if you have a story to share with the world, one rooted in empathy that encourages and empowers others to find light, and you’re ready to invest in the value of your story, then send me a dm or comment below and i can help you take that step. as a speaking coach for the #micdropworkshop , i’m offering free coaching sessions (normal value of $250) for anyone who signs up for our upcoming course by this sunday. check the link in my bio for more info. can’t wait to walk this journey with you!

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
qué difícil es trabajar en medios y tener que ver/leer la reacción de la gente ante un material, un posteo de casos como el de thelma fardín. 😞
'
la mayoría acaba criticándola por haberse callado, por haber hablado después de tantos años, por no haberse defendido y por tantas estupideces más...
'
de esa cantidad de comentarios, lo único que agradezco y celebro es que quienes los escribieron evidentemente no fueron víctimas de abuso o de intento de abuso sexual...
'
(y prefiero creer eso antes que imaginar que son abusadores)
'
si no, no estarían haciendo el ridículo...
si no, no la juzgarían...
si no, no se burlarían de una mujer que todavía tiene que revivir públicamente aquel doloroso episodio pa que la crean...
si no, se pondrían en su lugar e intentarían entenderla, querrían abrazarla, pedirle perdón en nombre del idiota que destruyó su adolescencia...
si no, por lo menos lo pensarían dos veces antes de mover los dedos pa escribir idioteces...
'
yo no dejo de admirar su valentía para exponerse al mundo y contar en detalles su desgracia. esa misma valentía que, por ejemplo, tuvieron las gimnastas de usa cuando en un juicio público, y también llorando hasta no poder hablar, revivieron los abusos que sufrieron de niñas...
'
¡no! no señor@s, no es fácil decir no (a cualquier edad), y mucho menos que te entiendan que no, es ¡no! 😡
'
fácil es juzgar, señalar con el dedo, hacer la vista gorda, decir lo que esta bien y lo que está mal "a según ustedes". fácil es ser valiente detrás de un teclado, de un teléfono...
'
#mirácómonosponemos #nonoscallamosmás #yositecreo #noesno #metoo

text:
2018. a year that will go down in history as the year of women. the year feminism fought back. i have been so inspired this year by the stories of empowered women fighting back against injustices and making sure their stories are heard. the past few days i’ve been keeping up with the jacob anderson case, and i believe it is time for me to share my story with the world.

i am a survivor of sexual assault and stalking from june. i learned the hard way that what we had wasn’t love like i though it was. it was lust under the guise of love. what angers me more than the mental and physical abuse i’ve endured by men is the way my university handled it when i spoke out and reported. 
university case determinations are based on the preponderance of evidence standard, meaning charges occur when they believe the event more likely than not occurred (a 51% chance). my case was settled on september 26. i went into the office and sat down in front of a 45-page report with the words not responsible in all caps and bolded. i had evidence and witness statements of the stalking, but was told in an interview that they “weren’t really as concerned with that as the assault.” therefore stalking wasn’t even listed under the charges, the one thing i had indisputable evidence for, but that wasn’t even what upset me the most.

in the beginning of the report they list staf 1.08 which contains the university’s definition of consent. 
consent is  defined as an uncoerced, enthusiastic “yes.” in my investigator’s summary of notes from one of the meetings with my respondent (my attacker) he wrote, “respondent states there was not “a verbal word ‘yes,’ but it was the same routine and she was engaged.” they acknowledge that consent was never asked for and that i never gave a verbal “yes,” but because it was the same routine and i was silent/absent of resistance they considered it consent. this was a lot to deal with. to sit across from a man and essentially be told my story was invalid. i’m here to share my story to show everyone that you are not alone. your story is valid whether you report or not. your trauma is valid and is not to be compared to others’. you are valid.
#metoo #believesurvivors

text:
l'attrice argentina thelma fardin, conosciuta per aver preso parte alla serie tv "il mondo di patty", ha denunciato un collega attore, juan darthés, accusandolo di averla violentata in nicaragua nel 2009, quando lei aveva 16 anni e lui 45. darthes era il promotore della serie, interpretata da giovani aspiranti attrici minorenni. le parole di fardin hanno suscitato immediatamente la solidarietà dell'associazione attrici argentine e oltre 100 donne che ne fanno parte si sono fatte fotografare con lei, in un gesto che oggi è sulle prime pagine di molti giornali a buenos aires. darthes ha negato i fatti, scrivendo su twitter: "è pazzesco, non è mai successo nulla". fardin ha spiegato di essersi convinta a parlare grazie al movimento niunamenos, versione argentina del #metoo di hollywood: ha trovato il coraggio di denunciare durante una conferenza stampa in un teatro della capitale argentina, mostrando un video molto forte, in cui tra le lacrime racconta i dettagli del presunto stupro, poi condiviso anche su instagram. "tornando dalla piscina mi sono accorta che mi si era smagnetizzata la scheda per aprire la porta dell'hotel", racconta thelma nel video. darthés le disse, afferma l'attrice, di andare in camera sua e chiedere per telefono che gliene fosse portata un'altra. "accettai", spiega thelma, "ma mentre ero al telefono ha cominciato a baciarmi sul collo e non si è fermato più". nel video fardin racconta tutti i particolari della violenza - portata a termine ma interrotta da qualcuno che bussò alla porta, dice - e dedica le ultime sequenze ai volti delle attrici solidali che guardando fissa la telecamera sfidano il presunto stupratore. durante la conferenza stampa è poi emerso che l'attore accusato del gesto avrebbe perfino partecipato alla realizzazione di uno spot del ministero dello sviluppo sociale contro la violenza di genere, che ora l'istituto nazionale delle donne avrebbe deciso di ritirare da tutti gli account dei suoi social network.

text:
"work we love, people we appreciate!"
.

featured this week: chris stark
.

christine stark is an award-winning writer, visual artist, national and international speaker of european, anishinaabe & cherokee ancestry. her first novel, nickels: a tale of dissociation, was a lambda literary finalist. she is also a co-editor of not for sale: feminists resisting prostitution and pornography; and a co-interviewer and co-author of ground-breaking research "garden of truth: the prostitution and trafficking of native women in minnesota". a two-time nominee for a pushcart prize, in 2012 she was named a “changemaker” by the women’s press. she has taught writing and humanity courses at a universities and community colleges for 16 years and worked as a two-spirit program director at minnesota indian women’s resource center. currently, she facilitates art and writing groups at an organization for prostituted and trafficked women in st. paul. for more information: www.christinestark.com

text:
‘my story is your story and your story is my story’
2018 has been one of the biggest and most transformational years for me and many of the women i know.

deep and profound changes are afoot both personally and collectively and i have had more enquires than ever before from women looking for a local circle where they can gather with other women and share what is going on for them in their world.

collectively, this year has also been a huge year for us to finally face and respond to the massive gaps in human equality relating to gender and race. it is no longer an option to sit silently by. we are being called (or called-out in some cases) to stand up, use our voices and take responsibility for our personal (and often unwitting) compliance. we are being called to support our sisters as they speak up and out against violence and abuse and oppression.

we are also being forced to take personal responsibility for the way we treat our planet and the different species we share it with, and to be more informed and activated about the current economic and politics state of the world. there is no doubt to anyone who is halfway awake that we are in a time of great change with an uncertain outcome.

that all being said, i also hold great hope that we are not too late to change the trajectory of these times. as i search my conscience for my own personal part to play, i keep coming back to the knowing that connection is key. connection to ourselves, connection to each other, connection to this beautiful planet and the other beings we share it with, and connection to spirit.

harambee in swahili, literally means ’pulling or working together' and i am seeing this everywhere. whether it is in women gathering in circles, young people mobilising over climate change and animal rights or women bravely standing up and saying #metoo.

as the sister circles continues to evolve, and more women meet in circle all around the world, we are gathering a great network of women who are taking responsibility for themselves and then turning around to assist our sisters.

text:
our #womancrushwednesday goes out to a woman whom @oprah calls a mentor-the brilliant, brave and barrier-busting @drmayaangelou! she was born in the segregated south and challenged assumptions about what poor black girls could do. she had an incredibly productive writing career, with 30 books to her credit, but she’s probably best known for her six memoirs-the first was “i know why the caged bird sings.” long before the #metoo movement, the book details her experience with sexual trauma-her mom’s boyfriend raped her when she was very young. he was tried and convicted but murdered before he could serve time. she didn’t speak for nearly five years, believing her voice killed him. she says only her love of literature brought back her voice. her first memoir became a best-seller, during a time when most publishers didn’t think black women’s lives were worthy of autobiography. she had several other jobs and broke many barriers - she was san francisco's first female african-american cable car conductor, at the age of 16. she was also one of the first african-american female members of the director's guild of america. her career in the arts wasn't limited to writing - maya angelou was also a singer, a calypso dancer and a broadway actress. she won three grammy awards for best spoken word albums, and she won a tony for her role in the 1972 play, look away. she also holds 50 honorary degrees.

in 1993, president-elect bill clinton invited her to read an original poem at his inauguration - only the second poet in american history to receive the honor. (know who the first poet was? and whose inauguration he read at? post your answer in the comments!) in 2011, former president barack obama awarded her the highest civilian honor -  the presidential medal of freedom. maya angelou was all about love and inclusivity: she believed we are more alike than unalike, regardless of our ethnic, religious and cultural differences. she died in 2014 at the age of 86. 
#wcw #womenempowerment #womeninspiringwomen #dogoodbegood @mistressmarquam @iammichaelfaith @m.k.ulta @annemarieluthro @evantia_maria @dirtgirl.bader.26

our  goes out to a woman whom  calls a mentor-the brilliant, brave and barrier-busting  she was born in the segregated south and challenged assumptions about what poor black girls could do. she had an incredibly productive writing career, with 30 books to her credit, but she’s probably best known for her six memoirs-the first was “i know why the caged bird sings.” long before the  movement, the book details her experience with sexual trauma-her mom’s boyfriend raped her when she was very young. he was tried and convicted but murdered before he could serve time. she didn’t speak for nearly five years, believing her voice killed him. she says only her love of literature brought back her voice. her first memoir became a best-seller, during a time when most publishers didn’t think black women’s lives were wohy of autobiography. she had several other jobs and broke many barriers - she was san francisco's first female african-american cable car conductor, at the age of 16. she was also one of the first african-american female members of the director's guild of america. her career in the as wasn't limited to writing - maya angelou was also a singer, a calypso dancer and a broadway actress. she won three grammy awards for best spoken word albums, and she won a tony for her role in the 1972 play, look away. she also holds 50 honorary degrees.

in 1993, president-elect bill clinton invited her to read an original poem at his inauguration - only the second poet in american history to receive the honor. (know who the first poet was? and whose inauguration he read at? post your answer in the comments!) in 2011, former president barack obama awarded her the highest civilian honor -  the presidential medal of freedom. maya angelou was all about love and inclusivity: she believed we are more alike than unalike, regardless of our ethnic, religious and cultural differences. she died in 2014 at the age of 86.
